1
00:00:00,391 --> 00:00:04,661
(Incheon Metropolitan City has extreme rides and the sea.)

2
00:00:05,601 --> 00:00:07,701
(Lying on the Incheon Seashore)

3
00:00:08,501 --> 00:00:11,601
(The results of the missions carried out at each spot...)

4
00:00:12,101 --> 00:00:14,471
(will decide how many sleep outdoors.)

5
00:00:15,241 --> 00:00:18,011
(If only to avoid sleeping outdoors)

6
00:00:18,681 --> 00:00:21,310
(They will hang on.)

7
00:00:21,311 --> 00:00:22,351
Fire!

8
00:00:24,321 --> 00:00:26,521
(They will overcome their fear of heights.)

9
00:00:26,921 --> 00:00:28,921
(They fought the best they could.)

10
00:00:29,591 --> 00:00:31,161
(But they kept failing.)

11
00:00:31,621 --> 00:00:33,591
(Even Se Yoon fell.)

12
00:00:34,391 --> 00:00:36,501
(3 people must sleep outdoors.)

13
00:00:37,231 --> 00:00:38,960
(The members have a visitor.)

14
00:00:38,961 --> 00:00:43,141
(Someone's mother?)

15
00:00:44,171 --> 00:00:46,611
(DinDin's mother appears.)

16
00:00:47,671 --> 00:00:51,481
(2 Days 1 Night)

17
00:00:51,781 --> 00:00:53,651
- Hey.
- You said you'd caught a cold.

18
00:00:54,581 --> 00:00:55,810
You're in trouble.

19
00:00:55,811 --> 00:00:56,950
(1 person is greatly perplexed.)

20
00:00:56,951 --> 00:00:59,850
(He'd publicly criticized DinDin's mother's kimchi.)

21
00:00:59,851 --> 00:01:02,590
(Did someone play with the food?)

22
00:01:02,591 --> 00:01:04,090
I did have a cold.

23
00:01:04,091 --> 00:01:05,660
I love your hairstyle.

24
00:01:05,661 --> 00:01:07,160
Mom, he called your food trash.

25
00:01:07,161 --> 00:01:08,690
(The Kid tattles right away.)

26
00:01:08,691 --> 00:01:11,130
- Don't eat it ever again.
- He called your kimchi trash.

27
00:01:11,131 --> 00:01:12,730
- I feel terrible.
- Hello, ma'am.

28
00:01:12,731 --> 00:01:14,531
He doesn't even know how to cook.

29
00:01:14,801 --> 00:01:15,870
Hello.

30
00:01:15,871 --> 00:01:17,370
It's nice to see you.

31
00:01:17,371 --> 00:01:19,000
The other way, Mom!

32
00:01:19,001 --> 00:01:20,371
- You looked away.
- Mom.

33
00:01:21,471 --> 00:01:23,681
(DinDin's staunch supporter)

34
00:01:24,211 --> 00:01:28,381
(The queen of home-cooked meals)

35
00:01:29,751 --> 00:01:34,221
(She has proven herself to be a great cook.)

36
00:01:35,921 --> 00:01:42,431
(She fed the members well.)

37
00:01:45,231 --> 00:01:48,201
(They even lost their minds.)

38
00:01:48,901 --> 00:01:50,341
(I love you, kiss, kiss.)

39
00:01:52,501 --> 00:01:56,211
(DinDin's mom, Ms. Kim Pan Rye)

40
00:01:56,611 --> 00:01:59,981
Hello, viewers of 2 Days 1 Night on KBS.

41
00:02:00,211 --> 00:02:03,280
The members and filming crew...

42
00:02:03,281 --> 00:02:05,121
all have a really hard time.

43
00:02:05,421 --> 00:02:09,860
I wanted to treat you all to a nice meal.

44
00:02:09,861 --> 00:02:12,290
That's why I'm back.

45
00:02:12,291 --> 00:02:14,291
I'm not overstaying my welcome.

46
00:02:15,061 --> 00:02:16,900
Ms. Kim's the best cook ever!

47
00:02:16,901 --> 00:02:17,931
Gosh, no.

48
00:02:18,601 --> 00:02:20,000
Your food is amazing.

49
00:02:20,001 --> 00:02:21,600
Mommy Kim's cooking is the best.

50
00:02:21,601 --> 00:02:22,931
I loved the braised ribs.

51
00:02:23,101 --> 00:02:24,200
Some of you...

52
00:02:24,201 --> 00:02:26,910
have tasted Ms. Kim's cooking.

53
00:02:26,911 --> 00:02:28,410
- Us three.
- Se Yoon...

54
00:02:28,411 --> 00:02:29,941
loved my mom's food.

55
00:02:30,111 --> 00:02:32,511
Jong Min complained so much that it wasn't to his taste.

56
00:02:32,841 --> 00:02:34,850
He said we should throw away the kimchi.

57
00:02:34,851 --> 00:02:36,680
He said that about my mom's food.

58
00:02:36,681 --> 00:02:37,821
Why did you say...

59
00:02:38,721 --> 00:02:40,620
- He said...
- I told him to buy kimchi instead.

60
00:02:40,621 --> 00:02:42,220
(They're both tattling now.)

61
00:02:42,221 --> 00:02:43,460
Do you remember any of the food?

62
00:02:43,461 --> 00:02:45,590
- The braised ribs.
- The braised ribs.

63
00:02:45,591 --> 00:02:47,090
- I still can't forget it.
- Oh, dear Lord.

64
00:02:47,091 --> 00:02:49,930
I can't understand how and why Im Cheol...

65
00:02:49,931 --> 00:02:51,160
- is so thin.
- He should be fat.

66
00:02:51,161 --> 00:02:53,200
- If I were him, I'd be...
- That's right.

67
00:02:53,201 --> 00:02:54,370
He doesn't eat much.

68
00:02:54,371 --> 00:02:55,470
He's spoiled rotten.

69
00:02:55,471 --> 00:02:56,540
- He's spoiled.
- Yes.

70
00:02:56,541 --> 00:02:57,670
(On his phone in front of a feast)

71
00:02:57,671 --> 00:02:59,371
That's why he didn't grow much.

72
00:02:59,941 --> 00:03:01,140
Recently, DinDin...

73
00:03:01,141 --> 00:03:03,040
- is thought to be well-mannered.
- Yes.

74
00:03:03,041 --> 00:03:04,640
- People love him now.
- Yes.

75
00:03:04,641 --> 00:03:07,250
How do you feel now that people think well of him?

76
00:03:07,251 --> 00:03:08,410
I'm cautious.

77
00:03:08,411 --> 00:03:09,750
- I see.
- She's cautious.

78
00:03:09,751 --> 00:03:11,320
Like I'm walking on thin ice.

79
00:03:11,321 --> 00:03:12,481
Walking on thin ice?

80
00:03:13,321 --> 00:03:17,121
I am very grateful, you know.

81
00:03:17,691 --> 00:03:21,160
Before I knew it, he reached his late thirties.

82
00:03:21,161 --> 00:03:22,161
Yes.

83
00:03:22,162 --> 00:03:24,561
The Im and Lee temperament in his blood came out.

84
00:03:25,801 --> 00:03:26,870
- It had been hidden?
- Yes.

85
00:03:26,871 --> 00:03:30,171
Before, I couldn't understand where he'd come from.

86
00:03:30,571 --> 00:03:31,940
"Is that really my son?"

87
00:03:31,941 --> 00:03:33,910
- I was embarrassed.
- She was embarrassed.

88
00:03:33,911 --> 00:03:35,370
He gave me such a hard time.

89
00:03:35,371 --> 00:03:37,140
- You prayed a lot for him.
- Yes.

90
00:03:37,141 --> 00:03:38,180
(He was tough to raise.)

91
00:03:38,181 --> 00:03:39,510
I thought I'd named him wrong,

92
00:03:39,511 --> 00:03:41,781
that he'd never grow up and become mature.

93
00:03:42,051 --> 00:03:43,150
He didn't grow up?

94
00:03:43,151 --> 00:03:44,681
That's what I prayed about.

95
00:03:44,881 --> 00:03:47,290
With her here, today's dinner will be awesome.

96
00:03:47,291 --> 00:03:49,450
- As she explained earlier, - Yes.

97
00:03:49,451 --> 00:03:52,291
DinDin's mother so graciously came over.

98
00:03:52,691 --> 00:03:54,861
Because you suffered a lot over the winter,

99
00:03:55,261 --> 00:03:56,460
she made japchae.

100
00:03:56,461 --> 00:03:57,730
- I love japchae.
- Octopus soup.

101
00:03:57,731 --> 00:03:58,800
- It's your favorite.
- Octopus soup?

102
00:03:58,801 --> 00:04:00,000
And braised ribs too.

103
00:04:00,001 --> 00:04:01,170
- Braised ribs?
- It's so good.

104
00:04:01,171 --> 00:04:02,470
She prepared a special meal...

105
00:04:02,471 --> 00:04:04,700
of invigorating spring dishes.

106
00:04:04,701 --> 00:04:05,770
My gosh.

107
00:04:05,771 --> 00:04:07,441
Ma'am, I love octopus soup.

108
00:04:07,711 --> 00:04:09,340
Do you? Eat all you want.

109
00:04:09,341 --> 00:04:12,010
- I like it that you eat well.
- I love to eat.

110
00:04:12,011 --> 00:04:13,380
- Eat all you can.
- I will.

111
00:04:13,381 --> 00:04:15,211
- I have something to say.
- Okay.

112
00:04:15,651 --> 00:04:19,951
Mom has been swiping my credit card like crazy recently.

113
00:04:20,551 --> 00:04:22,421
She went to some blue crab place,

114
00:04:22,591 --> 00:04:24,320
and then to some butcher.

115
00:04:24,321 --> 00:04:26,190
- Really?
- He called me.

116
00:04:26,191 --> 00:04:27,560
I kept getting texts.

117
00:04:27,561 --> 00:04:29,860
You spent a lot of money.

118
00:04:29,861 --> 00:04:31,000
(She must've spent a lot.)

119
00:04:31,001 --> 00:04:32,930
- He'll have been surprised.
- Why put it on my card?

120
00:04:32,931 --> 00:04:33,970
You paid for it?

121
00:04:33,971 --> 00:04:35,330
Why put it on my card?

122
00:04:35,331 --> 00:04:36,470
- It's not like that.
- Don't complain.

123
00:04:36,471 --> 00:04:37,641
The credit card...

124
00:04:37,801 --> 00:04:40,870
If they asked you to cook, you should've gotten their card.

125
00:04:40,871 --> 00:04:42,670
Why did you spend my money?

126
00:04:42,671 --> 00:04:44,180
Did you keep the receipts?

127
00:04:44,181 --> 00:04:45,510
- What?
- The receipts.

128
00:04:45,511 --> 00:04:46,850
Let's discuss that later.

129
00:04:46,851 --> 00:04:48,810
- I'll bill you people.
- Okay.

130
00:04:48,811 --> 00:04:50,850
- We'll reimburse you.
- She spent a fortune.

131
00:04:50,851 --> 00:04:52,120
Why mention money...

132
00:04:52,121 --> 00:04:53,420
- when she meant well?
- Yes.

133
00:04:53,421 --> 00:04:55,391
- What's wrong with him?
- Goodness.

134
00:04:55,591 --> 00:04:56,790
She spent hundreds of dollars...

135
00:04:56,791 --> 00:04:58,090
- at a blue crab place.
- About him.

136
00:04:58,091 --> 00:05:00,591
He acts like he's poor sometimes.

137
00:05:02,431 --> 00:05:04,000
(Bruised by his mom's exposé)

138
00:05:04,001 --> 00:05:05,330
You don't have to act like that now.

139
00:05:05,331 --> 00:05:06,460
- Yes.
- Come on.

140
00:05:06,461 --> 00:05:08,530
You don't know how expensive groceries are.

141
00:05:08,531 --> 00:05:09,531
But...

142
00:05:09,532 --> 00:05:10,540
You don't know...

143
00:05:10,541 --> 00:05:12,340
- how the prices are like.
- She bought...

144
00:05:12,341 --> 00:05:13,510
nicer stuff than what they used...

145
00:05:13,511 --> 00:05:15,070
on "Culinary Class Wars."

146
00:05:15,071 --> 00:05:16,580
- Wait.
- Dinner will be good.

147
00:05:16,581 --> 00:05:17,940
- Yes.
- It will be really good.

148
00:05:17,941 --> 00:05:21,011
KBS is the reason you make a living.

149
00:05:21,451 --> 00:05:22,481
Good point.

150
00:05:23,521 --> 00:05:26,620
(She brought lots of rice cake for the staff.)

151
00:05:26,621 --> 00:05:28,750
Thanks for the rice cake, ma'am.

152
00:05:28,751 --> 00:05:30,490
(We really enjoyed it.)

153
00:05:30,491 --> 00:05:31,661
It's really good.

154
00:05:34,131 --> 00:05:35,431
(You're the best.)

155
00:05:35,631 --> 00:05:37,261
Let's get into it, then.

156
00:05:38,731 --> 00:05:39,731
(We will begin in earnest now.)

157
00:05:39,732 --> 00:05:41,330
But she cooked for us. All of us should get to eat.

158
00:05:41,331 --> 00:05:42,970
- Of course. We ought to eat it.
- Right.

159
00:05:42,971 --> 00:05:44,700
- Let's not play any games.
- It will be rude otherwise.

160
00:05:44,701 --> 00:05:45,701
Seon Ho, you're worried...

161
00:05:45,702 --> 00:05:46,740
- you might not get to eat.
- Right.

162
00:05:46,741 --> 00:05:48,417
- We have to eat it no matter what.
- Right.

163
00:05:48,441 --> 00:05:49,711
DinDin paid for it.

164
00:05:49,841 --> 00:05:51,780
- We will begin...
- That's true.

165
00:05:51,781 --> 00:05:52,910
- It makes no sense...
- We'll begin?

166
00:05:52,911 --> 00:05:54,551
If I don't get to eat when I paid for it.

167
00:05:54,951 --> 00:05:57,220
But there are rules to follow on our show.

168
00:05:57,221 --> 00:05:58,250
All right. Let's begin.

169
00:05:58,251 --> 00:06:01,851
We will begin the Dinner Game in earnest now.

170
00:06:02,191 --> 00:06:03,791
- Members.
- What?

171
00:06:03,921 --> 00:06:05,220
- Please leave.
- My gosh.

172
00:06:05,221 --> 00:06:07,431
Why do we have to leave?

173
00:06:08,131 --> 00:06:09,630
- It's a game of wits.
- We'll stay out for a moment?

174
00:06:09,631 --> 00:06:10,760
(It looks like a game of wits.)

175
00:06:10,761 --> 00:06:13,100
- Let's go with the standard choice.
- Okay.

176
00:06:13,101 --> 00:06:14,101
The popular choice.

177
00:06:14,102 --> 00:06:16,270
I'm getting a feeling she might have to play too.

178
00:06:16,271 --> 00:06:18,601
Ma'am, please go with the standard choice.

179
00:06:18,901 --> 00:06:20,971
I can't play it if the game is too difficult.

180
00:06:21,841 --> 00:06:22,971
You can do this.

181
00:06:23,881 --> 00:06:26,140
Hey, it could be, "Pick the person she wants to feed the most."

182
00:06:26,141 --> 00:06:27,380
Don't you think so?

183
00:06:27,381 --> 00:06:28,580
Do we have to pick the same choice?

184
00:06:28,581 --> 00:06:30,221
We have to pick the most standard choice.

185
00:06:30,651 --> 00:06:31,820
All right. Let's begin.

186
00:06:31,821 --> 00:06:33,567
- Let's do it now. What is it?
- We'll begin right away.

187
00:06:33,591 --> 00:06:34,591
The Dinner Game is called...

188
00:06:34,592 --> 00:06:36,090
I'm Sure She's My Mom.

189
00:06:36,091 --> 00:06:37,190
You will do...

190
00:06:37,191 --> 00:06:38,590
a behavior prediction mission with DinDin's mother.

191
00:06:38,591 --> 00:06:40,130
- A behavior prediction mission?
- We have to predict her behavior?

192
00:06:40,131 --> 00:06:41,230
Is it similar to a mission we've played before?

193
00:06:41,231 --> 00:06:42,530
Do you remember the behavior prediction mission...

194
00:06:42,531 --> 00:06:44,211
- you played with each other?
- Yes, I do.

195
00:06:44,361 --> 00:06:46,031
The rules are the same.

196
00:06:46,531 --> 00:06:48,401
We'll present five questions.

197
00:06:48,701 --> 00:06:50,571
The number of correct answers will be...

198
00:06:50,971 --> 00:06:52,840
the number of members who will get to enjoy her food.

199
00:06:52,841 --> 00:06:54,710
(The number of correct answers will determine the number of eaters.)

200
00:06:54,711 --> 00:06:56,270
If we get 3 questions right, 2 people can't eat then?

201
00:06:56,271 --> 00:06:57,711
- Right.
- Gosh, that's cruel.

202
00:06:57,841 --> 00:06:59,441
Once the number of eaters is determined,

203
00:06:59,541 --> 00:07:01,127
we will then reveal the method that will decide...

204
00:07:01,151 --> 00:07:03,451
- who gets to eat dinner.
- Okay.

205
00:07:03,681 --> 00:07:05,280
Do they expect me to get it wrong? She's my mom.

206
00:07:05,281 --> 00:07:06,350
- Right.
- Okay. Let's do this.

207
00:07:06,351 --> 00:07:07,450
- Let's do it.
- Let's go.

208
00:07:07,451 --> 00:07:09,091
Here's the first question.

209
00:07:09,321 --> 00:07:10,691
- Do you think...
- Please.

210
00:07:11,361 --> 00:07:13,801
Pan Rye can successfully play defense against Director Joo...

211
00:07:14,191 --> 00:07:15,471
in the game of Cham, Cham, Cham?

212
00:07:15,591 --> 00:07:18,200
Gosh, since he keeps losing to the son,

213
00:07:18,201 --> 00:07:19,461
he'll try to beat the mother?

214
00:07:19,931 --> 00:07:21,001
That's too much.

215
00:07:22,101 --> 00:07:23,371
- Ma'am, - Yes.

216
00:07:23,571 --> 00:07:25,347
Do you know the game called Cham, Cham, Cham?

217
00:07:25,371 --> 00:07:26,740
- Yes, I do.
- Cham, cham, cham.

218
00:07:26,741 --> 00:07:29,141
- Cham, cham cham.
- You always lose to my son.

219
00:07:29,611 --> 00:07:31,111
- That's right.
- Yes.

220
00:07:31,611 --> 00:07:34,851
(Even his mother knows...)

221
00:07:35,011 --> 00:07:36,080
Cham, cham, cham.

222
00:07:36,081 --> 00:07:39,851
(about DinDin's complete victory against Director Joo.)

223
00:07:41,421 --> 00:07:45,291
(The ultimate boss of Cham, Cham, Cham)

224
00:07:45,561 --> 00:07:48,130
- The members will come back in.
- Okay.

225
00:07:48,131 --> 00:07:50,531
When they come in, you and I will play...

226
00:07:50,831 --> 00:07:52,260
Cham, Cham, Cham.

227
00:07:52,261 --> 00:07:53,701
- Really?
- Yes.

228
00:07:54,271 --> 00:07:56,841
But does she know how to play Cham, Cham, Cham?

229
00:07:57,071 --> 00:07:58,440
She can just turn her head sideways.

230
00:07:58,441 --> 00:07:59,700
- If the talent runs in the family, - Really?

231
00:07:59,701 --> 00:08:01,270
- I agree. She's DinDin's mother.
- she might be able to win.

232
00:08:01,271 --> 00:08:02,411
I doubt she'll lose.

233
00:08:02,871 --> 00:08:04,711
Come on. The talent must run in the family.

234
00:08:04,911 --> 00:08:06,381
The family of Cham, Cham, Cham?

235
00:08:06,581 --> 00:08:08,780
- Cham Family.
- DinDin has never lost.

236
00:08:08,781 --> 00:08:10,120
- There's no way of knowing.
- Here's what I know.

237
00:08:10,121 --> 00:08:11,451
She's not fast.

238
00:08:11,521 --> 00:08:12,850
- Older people react slowly.
- Right.

239
00:08:12,851 --> 00:08:14,250
When he says, "Cham, cham, cham,"

240
00:08:14,251 --> 00:08:15,920
- she might follow his hand.
- Right.

241
00:08:15,921 --> 00:08:17,961
Do you want to play a practice round?

242
00:08:18,321 --> 00:08:19,591
- Shall we?
- Yes.

243
00:08:19,821 --> 00:08:21,690
- Let's play one.
- Okay.

244
00:08:21,691 --> 00:08:23,461
All right. Here it goes.

245
00:08:23,661 --> 00:08:24,931
Cham, cham, cham.

246
00:08:25,101 --> 00:08:27,300
- Then I've lost, right?
- You can't do that. Right.

247
00:08:27,301 --> 00:08:28,741
- Right.
- Let's play one more time.

248
00:08:29,171 --> 00:08:30,371
Cham, cham, cham.

249
00:08:30,471 --> 00:08:32,640
(She lost again!)

250
00:08:32,641 --> 00:08:35,010
- I thought you'd go the other way.
- Yes?

251
00:08:35,011 --> 00:08:36,541
- You picked the same side.
- Right.

252
00:08:37,981 --> 00:08:41,081
(Hold on. Let's analyze the practice footage.)

253
00:08:41,781 --> 00:08:43,650
Cham, cham, cham.

254
00:08:43,651 --> 00:08:45,250
(She turned her head after Director Joo's hand moved.)

255
00:08:45,251 --> 00:08:46,827
When he says, "Cham, cham, cham," she might...

