But why did you pick Joon?

992
00:32:18,453 --> 00:32:20,162
Joon is powerful.

993
00:32:20,163 --> 00:32:21,422
- See? I told you.
- Right.

994
00:32:21,423 --> 00:32:22,722
- I said she'd pick Joon...
- Yes.

995
00:32:22,723 --> 00:32:24,162
- because he's strong.
- But...

996
00:32:24,163 --> 00:32:25,683
- Yes?
- why didn't you pick Jong Min?

997
00:32:26,193 --> 00:32:27,632
He just got married.

998
00:32:27,633 --> 00:32:29,762
- Honestly...
- She does have a point.

999
00:32:29,763 --> 00:32:31,403
Then what about Seon Ho?

1000
00:32:32,333 --> 00:32:34,372
He's so weak.

1001
00:32:34,373 --> 00:32:35,972
- I can't send him there.
- She's a mom.

1002
00:32:35,973 --> 00:32:37,342
She picked the two members...

1003
00:32:37,343 --> 00:32:38,912
most likely to survive on a deserted island.

1004
00:32:38,913 --> 00:32:40,612
- That was my point.
- We should've thought about that.

1005
00:32:40,613 --> 00:32:41,982
- What a bummer.
- We finished...

1006
00:32:41,983 --> 00:32:43,512
playing the Dinner Game.

1007
00:32:43,513 --> 00:32:45,453
You got three questions right.

1008
00:32:45,883 --> 00:32:49,552
So only three of you can eat dinner cooked by Pan Rye.

1009
00:32:49,553 --> 00:32:51,152
(What a bummer.)

1010
00:32:51,153 --> 00:32:53,693
- We must decide which three...
- I really need to eat.

1011
00:32:53,793 --> 00:32:55,223
Will eat dinner.

1012
00:32:56,063 --> 00:32:57,393
All right. Bring it in.

1013
00:32:57,663 --> 00:32:58,692
- What is it?
- What is it?

1014
00:32:58,693 --> 00:33:00,413
- It's a roulette.
- Great. This is better.

1015
00:33:00,903 --> 00:33:02,302
(The 3 chosen members will get to eat dinner.)

1016
00:33:02,303 --> 00:33:03,603
What about the last slot?

1017
00:33:04,303 --> 00:33:05,572
- Mom.
- Yes.

1018
00:33:05,573 --> 00:33:07,572
You can write down one name on the empty slot.

1019
00:33:07,573 --> 00:33:09,102
- The one you want to feed the most.
- The one you want to feed the most.

1020
00:33:09,103 --> 00:33:10,172
Among the five of us.

1021
00:33:10,173 --> 00:33:11,542
- Just write down anyone's name?
- Yes.

1022
00:33:11,543 --> 00:33:12,642
I must eat well, ma'am.

1023
00:33:12,643 --> 00:33:13,842
You're following the Mediterranean diet.

1024
00:33:13,843 --> 00:33:15,943
I'm getting old. You know?

1025
00:33:16,283 --> 00:33:19,853
When I skip a meal, it's not good for me. You know?

1026
00:33:20,523 --> 00:33:22,123
- Okay.
- Who is it?

1027
00:33:22,623 --> 00:33:23,922
Can I take a look?

1028
00:33:23,923 --> 00:33:25,192
- Let me see. Who is it?
- Two, three.

1029
00:33:25,193 --> 00:33:26,323
She must feel bad.

1030
00:33:27,163 --> 00:33:29,223
- Ma'am, gosh. You didn't have to.
- What?

1031
00:33:30,033 --> 00:33:31,933
- I feel bad.
- Why do you feel bad?

1032
00:33:32,963 --> 00:33:35,302
Then I'll try my best to get picked for dinner.

1033
00:33:35,303 --> 00:33:36,502
She sent you to a deserted island.

1034
00:33:36,503 --> 00:33:37,902
All right. Three of us can eat.

1035
00:33:37,903 --> 00:33:38,932
- Should we do it?
- Okay.

1036
00:33:38,933 --> 00:33:39,942
- I have to eat dinner today.
- Ma'am.

1037
00:33:39,943 --> 00:33:41,942
- Could you spin it hard?
- I really want to eat today.

1038
00:33:41,943 --> 00:33:43,413
- The first member.
- Here it goes.

1039
00:33:43,873 --> 00:33:45,213
I really want to eat her food.

1040
00:33:45,343 --> 00:33:46,842
- It will stop right away.
- I have a good feeling about this.

1041
00:33:46,843 --> 00:33:48,042
- Please.
- That's it.

1042
00:33:48,043 --> 00:33:49,043
- That's it.
- Please.

1043
00:33:49,044 --> 00:33:50,852
- Please let me win.
- Here it is.

1044
00:33:50,853 --> 00:33:52,413
- Yes. Gosh.
- It's me!

1045
00:33:52,813 --> 00:33:54,423
(Jong Min is chosen.)

1046
00:33:54,823 --> 00:33:56,382
(She bursts into laughter.)

1047
00:33:56,383 --> 00:33:58,053
It stops right away.

1048
00:33:59,393 --> 00:34:00,822
- Thank you for the meal.
- You must eat well...

1049
00:34:00,823 --> 00:34:02,763
since you're newly married.

1050
00:34:03,733 --> 00:34:04,762
- What?
- Gosh.

1051
00:34:04,763 --> 00:34:06,663
(She seems disappointed too.)

1052
00:34:07,003 --> 00:34:08,733
Gosh, he's so lucky.

1053
00:34:09,603 --> 00:34:11,302
- How does he always get so lucky?
- What?

1054
00:34:11,303 --> 00:34:13,403
I don't know. She picked me.

1055
00:34:13,873 --> 00:34:15,973
- I didn't ask her to pick me.
- My gosh.

1056
00:34:16,573 --> 00:34:17,742
She picked me.

1057
00:34:17,743 --> 00:34:19,072
- Three of us can eat.
- Oh, no.

1058
00:34:19,073 --> 00:34:21,042
- We still have a chance.
- All right.

1059
00:34:21,043 --> 00:34:22,742
- Okay. There are 2 more seats left.
- Let's do it 1 more time.

1060
00:34:22,743 --> 00:34:24,012
- Japchae and braised ribs.
- One,

1061
00:34:24,013 --> 00:34:25,412
- You wrote my name down.
- two, three.

1062
00:34:25,413 --> 00:34:26,452
All right.

1063
00:34:26,453 --> 00:34:28,023
- Let's go. Please.
- Gosh.

1064
00:34:28,983 --> 00:34:30,993
Here it is! It's my name!

1065
00:34:31,893 --> 00:34:34,393
(The arrow is shaking between Se Yoon and Joon.)

1066
00:34:34,723 --> 00:34:36,593
(Will it be Se Yoon or Joon?)

1067
00:34:38,763 --> 00:34:40,532
(Se Yoon)

1068
00:34:40,533 --> 00:34:42,732
(Moon Se Yoon has been chosen.)

1069
00:34:42,733 --> 00:34:44,203
- It's Se Yoon!
- Oh, yes!

1070
00:34:44,273 --> 00:34:46,603
It's Se Yoon. Ms. Kim, it's me and Se Yoon.

1071
00:34:47,103 --> 00:34:50,043
- It's unbelievable.
- That's great. I'm happy for you.

1072
00:34:50,273 --> 00:34:51,273
You did a great job earlier.

1073
00:34:51,274 --> 00:34:52,772
(He's getting emotional.)

1074
00:34:52,773 --> 00:34:54,642
- You did a great job.
- You have to spin it once again.

1075
00:34:54,643 --> 00:34:55,743
My belly hurt so much.

1076
00:34:55,783 --> 00:34:56,852
Good job doing sit-ups.

1077
00:34:56,853 --> 00:34:59,182
- I did it after many years.
- Great job.

1078
00:34:59,183 --> 00:35:01,652
- He did it more than 40 times.
- Thank you, Ms. Kim.

1079
00:35:01,653 --> 00:35:03,992
- One, two...
- She must want her son to eat.

1080
00:35:03,993 --> 00:35:05,992
- No, that's okay.
- Is it okay if he can't eat?

1081
00:35:05,993 --> 00:35:06,993
Right now... Oh, my.

1082
00:35:06,994 --> 00:35:08,162
(Mom, it's not okay.)

1083
00:35:08,163 --> 00:35:10,933
She spun it. All right. Here we go.

1084
00:35:11,463 --> 00:35:12,532
We have one last spot.

1085
00:35:12,533 --> 00:35:14,363
Who will win the last spot?

1086
00:35:14,933 --> 00:35:17,802
- Will it be her son or his friend?
- Who will it be?

1087
00:35:17,803 --> 00:35:19,832
- Ms. Kim spun it.
- Who will it be?

1088
00:35:19,833 --> 00:35:22,642
- Right now...
- Who is it?

1089
00:35:22,643 --> 00:35:23,672
Oh, it's been decided.

1090
00:35:23,673 --> 00:35:24,943
- It's Joon.
- It's Joon.

1091
00:35:25,073 --> 00:35:26,813
(Lee Joon has been chosen.)

1092
00:35:26,913 --> 00:35:29,443
(He's deeply moved.)

1093
00:35:30,753 --> 00:35:32,882
- I feel bad for Seon Ho.
- My goodness. Look at this.

1094
00:35:32,883 --> 00:35:35,352
- Look whom Ms. Kim chose.
- Ms. Kim...

1095
00:35:35,353 --> 00:35:36,892
- Ms. Kim...
- She chose...

1096
00:35:36,893 --> 00:35:38,553
the three oldest members.

1097
00:35:38,593 --> 00:35:40,822
I really want my money back for the ingredients.

1098
00:35:40,823 --> 00:35:43,023
- Sure. We'll give you the money.
- Come on. Seriously.

1099
00:35:43,093 --> 00:35:44,763
- All right, everyone.
- Ms. Kim.

1100
00:35:45,833 --> 00:35:47,333
- He's a good son.
- Everyone.

1101
00:35:47,703 --> 00:35:50,372
You will start eating once the food is ready.

1102
00:35:50,373 --> 00:35:51,402
- Okay.
- Okay.

1103
00:35:51,403 --> 00:35:53,109
(What food did Pan Rye prepare for the dinner?)

1104
00:35:53,133 --> 00:35:55,343
(Pan Rye's dishes will be revealed right now.)

1105
00:35:56,243 --> 00:35:59,773
(She starts by grilling thick slices of largehead hairtail.)

1106
00:36:00,843 --> 00:36:03,813
(She heats up the braised ribs that she made at home.)

1107
00:36:04,583 --> 00:36:07,263
(She cuts soy sauce marinated crab so that they can eat it easily.)

1108
00:36:10,023 --> 00:36:14,223
(She deep-fries shrimps on the spot to ensure a crunchy texture.)

1109
00:36:14,993 --> 00:36:17,963
(Every dish has been prepared by Pan Rye.)

1110
00:36:18,293 --> 00:36:21,333
It's a shame that only three of them get to eat my food.

1111
00:36:22,003 --> 00:36:23,473
I should've done a better job.

1112
00:36:23,573 --> 00:36:25,872
I feel sorry for Seon Ho.

1113
00:36:25,873 --> 00:36:29,203
I can always cook for my son, so that's okay.

1114
00:36:29,743 --> 00:36:32,242
- Ms. Kim.
- Yes? Come on in.

1115
00:36:32,243 --> 00:36:33,819
- We're here... Oh, my.
- You're here already.

1116
00:36:33,843 --> 00:36:35,482
- This is amazing.
- I hope you enjoy my food.

1117
00:36:35,483 --> 00:36:36,542
(Something catches the members' eyes.)

1118
00:36:36,543 --> 00:36:37,689
- Oh, my.
- Look at the hairtail.

1119
00:36:37,713 --> 00:36:38,882
(A wide variety of side dishes)

1120
00:36:38,883 --> 00:36:40,552
You're deep-frying it right here.

1121
00:36:40,553 --> 00:36:42,422
- Let's move the food.
- Shall we move the food there?

1122
00:36:42,423 --> 00:36:45,092
- Can you put these two...
- Yes.

1123
00:36:45,093 --> 00:36:47,093
- on a plate, please?
- Sure.

1124
00:36:47,223 --> 00:36:48,223
We'll help you, Ms. Kim.

1125
00:36:48,293 --> 00:36:50,262
- The food looks crazy good.
- I'll bring a tray.

1126
00:36:50,263 --> 00:36:52,162
How did she make all these dishes? I'm so amazed.

1127
00:36:52,163 --> 00:36:54,062
Be sure to plate them beautifully, Se Yoon.

1128
00:36:54,063 --> 00:36:55,362
- Yes, I'll do that.
- Okay.

1129
00:36:55,363 --> 00:36:56,402
Scoop the rice into bowls, too.

1130
00:36:56,403 --> 00:36:58,002
- Should we scoop the rice too?
- Yes.

1131
00:36:58,003 --> 00:36:59,102
A moderate serving would be enough.

1132
00:36:59,103 --> 00:37:00,902
- This much?
- I'll mainly eat the side dishes.

1133
00:37:00,903 --> 00:37:02,003
- Okay.
- Good.

1134
00:37:02,103 --> 00:37:05,013
- DinDin is so blessed.
- Indeed.

1135
00:37:05,273 --> 00:37:07,612
- How did she make all this food?
- Can you help me with this?

1136
00:37:07,613 --> 00:37:10,212
- Exactly.
- It took me five days.

1137
00:37:10,213 --> 00:37:11,582
- Five days?
- That's incredible.

1138
00:37:11,583 --> 00:37:14,552
- You guys always work so hard.
- This is insane.

1139
00:37:14,553 --> 00:37:16,652
So do the staff members.

1140
00:37:16,653 --> 00:37:17,753
Thank you so much, Ms. Kim.

1141
00:37:18,653 --> 00:37:20,052
- I think you can go now.
- Should I go?

1142
00:37:20,053 --> 00:37:21,453
There's deep-fried food back there.

1143
00:37:22,823 --> 00:37:25,593
(Jong Min leaves with the first tray.)

1144
00:37:25,833 --> 00:37:27,203
Look how big the hairtail is.

1145
00:37:28,133 --> 00:37:29,163
Oh, my.

1146
00:37:31,333 --> 00:37:32,372
It's amazing.

1147
00:37:32,373 --> 00:37:34,472
- No way.
- This is driving me crazy.

1148
00:37:34,473 --> 00:37:35,713
- Look at that.
- It's amazing.

1149
00:37:36,143 --> 00:37:38,424
Whom should I request the money from for the ingredients?

1150
00:37:38,473 --> 00:37:41,683
I just checked my credit card records.

1151
00:37:41,743 --> 00:37:43,012
It's like we're having a village party.

1152
00:37:43,013 --> 00:37:44,653
(Seon Ho wants to cry.)

1153
00:37:45,613 --> 00:37:46,923
Isn't this amazing?

1154
00:37:47,453 --> 00:37:49,523
I'm sorry, Seon Ho.

1155
00:37:49,823 --> 00:37:51,023
Gosh. The food smells so good.

1156
00:37:52,453 --> 00:37:53,593
Oh, gosh. Ms. Kim.

1157
00:37:53,623 --> 00:37:55,662
- Seon Ho, I'm sorry for you.
- The food smells so good.

1158
00:37:55,663 --> 00:37:57,962
I should've given you deep-fried shrimp secretly.

1159
00:37:57,963 --> 00:37:59,063
This looks amazing.

1160
00:37:59,163 --> 00:38:01,132
I'll scoop out some small octopus so you can have it.

1161
00:38:01,133 --> 00:38:02,133
(She offers small octopus secretly.)

1162
00:38:02,134 --> 00:38:03,573
- I can't eat it.
- You can't?

1163
00:38:03,973 --> 00:38:05,003
I'll be scolded.

1164
00:38:05,673 --> 00:38:06,673
(But he can't take his eyes off the food.)

1165
00:38:06,674 --> 00:38:07,914
- It must be so tasty.
- Sorry?

1166
00:38:08,303 --> 00:38:09,672
Oh, dear. I feel so bad for you.

1167
00:38:09,673 --> 00:38:11,642
Visit DinDin at his house sometime.

1168
00:38:11,643 --> 00:38:12,912
Can you please cook for me sometime?

1169
00:38:12,913 --> 00:38:13,982
You can have my food at DinDin's house.

1170
00:38:13,983 --> 00:38:15,959
I'll visit your house by myself, even without DinDin.

1171
00:38:15,983 --> 00:38:17,213
Okay. I'll cook for you.

1172
00:38:17,483 --> 00:38:20,922
(The guy whose presence isn't even required is totally upset.)

1173
00:38:20,923 --> 00:38:22,559
My mom worked hard to make all this food.

1174
00:38:22,583 --> 00:38:23,623
I'm sorry.

1175
00:38:24,523 --> 00:38:25,823
Then let me eat some too.

1176
00:38:26,593 --> 00:38:28,822
Let me eat some since my mom worked hard.

1177
00:38:28,823 --> 00:38:31,833
- I'm sorry.
- We have rules to follow.

1178
00:38:31,933 --> 00:38:34,103
Isn't this the best dinner ever on 2 Days 1 Night?

1179
00:38:34,203 --> 00:38:36,262
- The best dinner ever, indeed.
- Stop talking and put it down.

1180
00:38:36,263 --> 00:38:38,032
- It's peerless.
- You might spit in the soup.

1181
00:38:38,033 --> 00:38:39,303
It's number one.

1182
00:38:39,703 --> 00:38:40,942
Nothing can defeat this.

1183
00:38:40,943 --> 00:38:42,979
- It's absolutely number one.
- We should turn it on.

1184
00:38:43,003 --> 00:38:44,803
- You should start eating.
- Ms. Kim is here.

1185
00:38:44,943 --> 00:38:46,783
- Start eating.
- Thank you for this, Ms. Kim.

1186
00:38:47,013 --> 00:38:49,442
- Ms. Kim, this is unbelievable.
- It's unbelievable.

1187
00:38:49,443 --> 00:38:50,913
- I'm completely amazed.
- Oh, my.

1188
00:38:51,013 --> 00:38:52,752
I hope it's tasty.

1189
00:38:52,753 --> 00:38:55,283
- It must be tasty.
- I put a lot of effort into this.

1190
00:38:56,023 --> 00:38:59,353
(Let us show you the 20-dish feast that Pan Rye prepared with love.)

1191
00:39:00,053 --> 00:39:02,623
(Braised ribs that look juicy)

1192
00:39:03,193 --> 00:39:05,332
(Golden brown, plump hairtail)

1193
00:39:05,333 --> 00:39:07,532
She's amazing. How did she make all this food?

1194
00:39:07,533 --> 00:39:09,362
No one else can do this.

1195
00:39:09,363 --> 00:39:11,072
- My mom is nothing compared to her.
- The same goes for my mom.

1196
00:39:11,073 --> 00:39:12,749
(Soy sauce marinated crab bursting with roe)

1197
00:39:12,773 --> 00:39:14,572
She made so much food. We might not be able to finish it all.

1198
00:39:14,573 --> 00:39:17,843
(And a wide variety of side dishes that fill the table)

1199
00:39:18,343 --> 00:39:21,112
(This is a feast...)

1200
00:39:21,113 --> 00:39:25,712
(of invigorating foods to welcome spring.)

1201
00:39:25,713 --> 00:39:28,852
Wouldn't it be better to move this to the side?

1202
00:39:28,853 --> 00:39:30,422
- Let's move the soup to the side.
- I'll scoop it out for you guys.

1203
00:39:30,423 --> 00:39:31,543
- Right.
- That'd be better.

1204
00:39:31,723 --> 00:39:34,222
- Let's rearrange the dishes.
- Let's move these around a bit.

1205
00:39:34,223 --> 00:39:37,062
- Let's... You know...
- What are these, Ms. Kim?

1206
00:39:37,063 --> 00:39:39,362
I brought some extra food in case there wasn't enough of it.

1207
00:39:39,363 --> 00:39:40,702
- I'll put the tray over there.
- Okay.

1208
00:39:40,703 --> 00:39:41,909
- They might eat some secretly.
- Okay.

1209
00:39:41,933 --> 00:39:43,433
The rice is for us.

1210
00:39:45,173 --> 00:39:47,743
Not eating this food is a sin.

1211
00:39:47,973 --> 00:39:49,202
- Director Joo.
- Yes?

1212
00:39:49,203 --> 00:39:51,942
How nice would it be if they could all enjoy the food?

1213
00:39:51,943 --> 00:39:53,272
Can you allow at least one more member to eat?

1214
00:39:53,273 --> 00:39:54,412
I'm very sorry,

1215
00:39:54,413 --> 00:39:57,013
but we have our own rules on this show.

1216
00:39:57,253 --> 00:39:59,012
(Please scold him.)

1217
00:39:59,013 --> 00:40:00,052
- We're embarrassed too, Ms. Kim.
- Exactly.

1218
00:40:00,053 --> 00:40:01,922
- He's so pitiful.
- It's so...

1219
00:40:01,923 --> 00:40:04,622
Look into Seon Ho's eyes.

1220
00:40:04,623 --> 00:40:05,623
It breaks my heart, but...

1221
00:40:05,623 --> 00:40:06,623
(Sad and desperate)

1222
00:40:06,624 --> 00:40:07,662
There's nothing we can do. Rules are rules.

1223
00:40:07,663 --> 00:40:09,823
This isn't our first time, Ms. Kim.

1224
00:40:09,963 --> 00:40:10,993
We're okay with it.

1225
00:40:11,063 --> 00:40:13,493
We have invigorating foods and all kinds of tasty foods.

1226
00:40:14,103 --> 00:40:15,933
We'll start eating once we get the soup.

1227
00:40:16,133 --> 00:40:20,233
(The first dish, octopus soup, that caught Se Yoon's eyes)

1228
00:40:21,003 --> 00:40:23,402
- This is a thin-legged octopus.
- It's hard to get.

1229
00:40:23,403 --> 00:40:26,473
- Abalone?
- Look how big the abalone is.

1230
00:40:26,713 --> 00:40:29,113
Here. Scoop out some scallops from the bottom.

1231
00:40:29,443 --> 00:40:30,652
(DinDin helps his mom even though he can't eat the food.)

1232
00:40:30,653 --> 00:40:31,912
- Scoop some out.
- It's for us.

1233
00:40:31,913 --> 00:40:34,252
(He scoops out the broth for the older members.)

1234
00:40:34,253 --> 00:40:37,523
- Ms. Kim, you should eat with us.
- Right. Please eat with us.

1235
00:40:37,593 --> 00:40:39,722
- She didn't eat any last time.
- Right.

1236
00:40:39,723 --> 00:40:41,592
Watching you guys enjoy my food...

1237
00:40:41,593 --> 00:40:43,062
- will make me feel full.
- But you should...

1238
00:40:43,063 --> 00:40:44,823
- Can we eat now, Ms. Kim?
- Can we eat now?

1239
00:40:45,033 --> 00:40:46,462
- One, two, three.
- Okay.

1240
00:40:46,463 --> 00:40:48,409
- Thank you for the food, Ms. Kim.
- Thank you for the food.

1241
00:40:48,433 --> 00:40:50,162
- Please enjoy.
- We'll enjoy it.

1242
00:40:50,163 --> 00:40:51,903
You all worked hard.

1243
00:40:52,633 --> 00:40:56,473
(They have a spoonful of the broth of the octopus soup first.)

1244
00:41:01,043 --> 00:41:02,242
- It's so refreshing.
- I feel like...

1245
00:41:02,243 --> 00:41:04,683
- I feel like my body is melting.
- Is the soup salty enough?

1246
00:41:04,813 --> 00:41:06,733
- It's amazing.
- The saltiness is just perfect.

1247
00:41:07,023 --> 00:41:08,452
What's in it? Is it wild chive?

1248
00:41:08,453 --> 00:41:11,353
- Yes. I also put in water parsley, - I can smell wild chive.

1249
00:41:11,653 --> 00:41:13,452
Green onion, and...

1250
00:41:13,453 --> 00:41:15,592
(The wild chive and water parsley that are in season...)

1251
00:41:15,593 --> 00:41:19,463
(give the dish piquant and refreshing flavors.)

1252
00:41:19,493 --> 00:41:20,833
I can't believe I can't eat that.

1253
00:41:20,963 --> 00:41:23,503
(Refreshing)

1254
00:41:23,933 --> 00:41:25,032
This is just amazing.

1255
00:41:25,033 --> 00:41:27,142
(Se Yoon puts the whole thin-legged octopus in his mouth.)

1256
00:41:27,143 --> 00:41:29,403
This is like a meal for a king.

1257
00:41:29,843 --> 00:41:31,742
(The chewy texture makes him feel grateful.)

1258
00:41:31,743 --> 00:41:32,973
This is incredible.

1259
00:41:34,183 --> 00:41:35,843
Mom, do you want some broth?

1260
00:41:36,113 --> 00:41:37,412
- No, I'm good.
- Have some broth, at least.

1261
00:41:37,413 --> 00:41:38,953
Ms. Kim, please have some food.

1262
00:41:39,083 --> 00:41:40,083
- Mom, - You worked so hard to make this.

1263
00:41:40,084 --> 00:41:42,183
- you might get sick again.
- I won't.

1264
00:41:42,983 --> 00:41:45,692
- I'm staying mentally tough.
- This is so good.

1265
00:41:45,693 --> 00:41:48,462
Joon, try soy sauce marinated crab...

1266
00:41:48,463 --> 00:41:50,693
I mean, try the sauce mixed with this.

1267
00:41:51,093 --> 00:41:52,962
Did you make the soy sauce marinated crab too?

1268
00:41:52,963 --> 00:41:56,862
Of course. It tastes best five days after it's made.

1269
00:41:56,863 --> 00:41:58,579
- Five days after it's made.
- She put in a lot of effort.

1270
00:41:58,603 --> 00:42:02,603
(He sucks the plump crab meat and the moist, tasty sauce.)

1271
00:42:03,003 --> 00:42:05,213
(Frown of truthful joy)

1272
00:42:05,943 --> 00:42:09,083
(Doesn't it look delicious?)

1273
00:42:10,243 --> 00:42:13,013
(Jong Min sucks the crab meat too.)

1274
00:42:13,413 --> 00:42:15,052
- Oh, my.
- Ms. Kim,

1275
00:42:15,053 --> 00:42:17,093
this soy sauce marinated crab is just salty enough.

1276
00:42:17,493 --> 00:42:19,092
It's just salty enough. How did she do that?

1277
00:42:19,093 --> 00:42:20,969
(Its saltiness is just right, and it has rich umami.)

1278
00:42:20,993 --> 00:42:23,693
(This is why it's considered one of the best side dishes.)

1279
00:42:24,433 --> 00:42:25,962
(Soy sauce marinated crab and rice)

1280
00:42:25,963 --> 00:42:27,402
My, this tastes like paradise.

1281
00:42:27,403 --> 00:42:28,833
(It's an incredible combination.)

1282
00:42:28,903 --> 00:42:31,332
- Jong Min, you like this. Here.
- It's so good.

1283
00:42:31,333 --> 00:42:32,573
Thank you so much, Ms. Kim.

1284
00:42:32,603 --> 00:42:34,203
- Jong Min likes japchae.
- Eat a lot.

1285
00:42:34,543 --> 00:42:36,402
It's the best I've ever tasted. I'm being honest.

1286
00:42:36,403 --> 00:42:38,213
- It's the best. Yes.
- Really?

1287
00:42:38,413 --> 00:42:40,272
- Awesome.
- It's so tasty.

1288
00:42:40,273 --> 00:42:41,743
The japchae is awesome.

1289
00:42:42,083 --> 00:42:44,413
I don't think Se Yoon ate any hairtail.

1290
00:42:45,313 --> 00:42:48,583
(I shall repay her for her thoughtfulness.)

1291
00:42:48,983 --> 00:42:50,752
Make sure to dip the deep-fried shrimp...

1292
00:42:50,753 --> 00:42:52,523
- in the peanut sauce.
- Yes, ma'am.

1293
00:42:52,953 --> 00:42:55,363
(Crunchy)

1294
00:42:56,423 --> 00:42:57,983
- How does it taste?
- That's not true.

1295
00:42:58,233 --> 00:43:00,532
I often order deep-fried shrimp at a restaurant...

1296
00:43:00,533 --> 00:43:02,163
for my children.

1297
00:43:02,633 --> 00:43:03,993
This is the best I've ever tasted.

1298
00:43:04,133 --> 00:43:05,333
Seriously. Try it.

1299
00:43:05,773 --> 00:43:07,972
Se Yoon, try a big piece of rib.

1300
00:43:07,973 --> 00:43:10,302
- This is driving me nuts.
- He can eat on his own. Stop it.

1301
00:43:10,303 --> 00:43:11,872
But he hasn't tried it yet.

1302
00:43:11,873 --> 00:43:13,372
- I mean, it's...
- Just leave him be.

1303
00:43:13,373 --> 00:43:14,912
- It's far from him.
- DinDin, don't be like that.

1304
00:43:14,913 --> 00:43:16,842
- It's far from him.
- Her words make it even better.

1305
00:43:16,843 --> 00:43:18,613
- He'd eat it however far it is.
- Right.

1306
00:43:19,583 --> 00:43:21,382
(It sure is true.)

1307
00:43:21,383 --> 00:43:22,522
- He'd eat it however far it is.
- The side dishes also...

1308
00:43:22,523 --> 00:43:23,653
Was it when we...

1309
00:43:23,993 --> 00:43:25,992
Did Ms. Kim join us for the shoot when we went to the school?

1310
00:43:25,993 --> 00:43:27,223
Look how big the meat is.

1311
00:43:28,093 --> 00:43:30,593
(He's preparing to enjoy it in the best way.)

1312
00:43:31,663 --> 00:43:35,233
(He covers the meat with kimchi.)

1313
00:43:35,333 --> 00:43:37,802
Ms. Kim, the braised ribs were my favorite.

1314
00:43:37,803 --> 00:43:39,403
- He'll give a performance.
- Ms. Kim...

1315
00:43:39,773 --> 00:43:40,872
That's good.

1316
00:43:40,873 --> 00:43:42,342
(Putting it all in his mouth)

1317
00:43:42,343 --> 00:43:44,142
All my hard work is paying off.

1318
00:43:44,143 --> 00:43:46,743
- It's really tasty.
- It's so good, Ms. Kim.

1319
00:43:47,543 --> 00:43:50,012
(Jong Min has a bite of meat.)

1320
00:43:50,013 --> 00:43:51,213
(Impressed)

1321
00:43:52,053 --> 00:43:53,773
- It just falls off the bone.
- The meat...

1322
00:43:54,053 --> 00:43:56,022
started melting in my mouth once I put it in.

1323
00:43:56,023 --> 00:43:57,122
(The meat is melting in my mouth.)

1324
00:43:57,123 --> 00:43:58,823
- There's a reason for that.
- What is it?

1325
00:43:59,023 --> 00:44:01,593
I scored the meat in a crosshatch pattern.

1326
00:44:01,693 --> 00:44:03,162
- Oh, I see.
- Really?

1327
00:44:03,163 --> 00:44:04,662
- Because it's thick.
- Right.

1328
00:44:04,663 --> 00:44:07,032
It was this thick, but as soon as I took a bite,

1329
00:44:07,033 --> 00:44:08,103
it fell apart.

1330
00:44:09,703 --> 00:44:12,133
(Joon takes a bite too.)

1331
00:44:12,403 --> 00:44:13,973
The braised ribs are awesome.

1332
00:44:15,243 --> 00:44:17,143
You bought the ribs with Cheol's money.

1333
00:44:18,143 --> 00:44:19,613
My, it's so good.

1334
00:44:19,673 --> 00:44:22,783
I'm so embarrassed. Gosh.

1335
00:44:23,283 --> 00:44:24,483
(Sighing)

1336
00:44:26,483 --> 00:44:29,383
I've never had a meltdown like this on this show, right?

1337
00:44:30,153 --> 00:44:31,153
(It's understandable because next to the feast...)

1338
00:44:31,154 --> 00:44:32,252
That's not true.

1339
00:44:32,253 --> 00:44:33,823
(Blanking out)

1340
00:44:34,493 --> 00:44:36,774
I don't know about everything else, but this is so cruel.

1341
00:44:37,333 --> 00:44:38,632
- I feel so sorry for you two.
- This is so good.

1342
00:44:38,633 --> 00:44:40,963
Can't you at least have some broth?

1343
00:44:41,303 --> 00:44:43,563
Can't I give them just one deep-fried shrimp each?

1344
00:44:44,273 --> 00:44:46,302
(He doesn't know what to do.)

1345
00:44:46,303 --> 00:44:48,103
Mom, my vision is blurry.

1346
00:44:48,643 --> 00:44:49,942
I can't see clearly.

1347
00:44:49,943 --> 00:44:51,712
He's so hungry that he can't see clearly.

1348
00:44:51,713 --> 00:44:53,342
I'm hungry, and I didn't get enough sleep.

1349
00:44:53,343 --> 00:44:55,082
- You can't see clearly?
- And I caught a cold too.

1350
00:44:55,083 --> 00:44:58,712
Exactly. They need to eat some food to get some energy.

1351
00:44:58,713 --> 00:45:00,083
This is so mean.

1352
00:45:02,653 --> 00:45:06,222
- I bet DinDin made her say this.
- I thought that Director Joo...

1353
00:45:06,223 --> 00:45:08,762
was a very nice person, but he's actually not.

1354
00:45:08,763 --> 00:45:09,763
My gosh. Seriously.

1355
00:45:09,764 --> 00:45:11,462
My impression on him changed completely.

1356
00:45:11,463 --> 00:45:15,103
I feel so sorry for my sons here.

1357
00:45:15,533 --> 00:45:17,533
I was wrong about Director Joo.

1358
00:45:18,033 --> 00:45:19,902
Pan Rye, I have an idea. You did a great job...

1359
00:45:19,903 --> 00:45:21,342
when we played Cham, Cham, Cham.

1360
00:45:21,343 --> 00:45:23,372
Let's play another round.

1361
00:45:23,373 --> 00:45:24,842
And if you win by defending successfully,

1362
00:45:24,843 --> 00:45:27,712
we'll give them a small dish...

1363
00:45:27,713 --> 00:45:29,673
- Sounds great.
- so that they can eat some food.

1364
00:45:29,743 --> 00:45:31,013
We still have a lot of food.

1365
00:45:31,213 --> 00:45:33,152
- A small dish?
- It's okay.

1366
00:45:33,153 --> 00:45:34,182
The octopus soup alone would be enough.

1367
00:45:34,183 --> 00:45:36,383
Right. One dish would be enough.

1368
00:45:37,123 --> 00:45:38,923
(Her maternal instinct is roaring to life.)

1369
00:45:38,993 --> 00:45:40,422
- Good luck, Pan Rye.
- Close...

1370
00:45:40,423 --> 00:45:41,992
- Close your eyes.
- Okay.

1371
00:45:41,993 --> 00:45:43,023
You've got this, Ms. Kim!

1372
00:45:43,093 --> 00:45:44,932
She turned her head to the left and won earlier.

1373
00:45:44,933 --> 00:45:46,262
- Since you said such a thing, - Don't say such a thing.

1374
00:45:46,263 --> 00:45:48,533
Director Joo will try to outsmart me.

1375
00:45:49,233 --> 00:45:50,803
- Close your eyes.
- Gosh, seriously.

1376
00:45:51,273 --> 00:45:52,302
(She's determined to feed her sons.)

1377
00:45:52,303 --> 00:45:53,432
She's concentrating.

1378
00:45:53,433 --> 00:45:55,472
All right. We'll begin now.

1379
00:45:55,473 --> 00:45:56,031
(Round 2, Pan Rye versus Director Joo)

1380
00:45:56,034 --> 00:45:57,127
All right. We'll begin now.

1381
00:45:57,136 --> 00:45:58,484
(Round 2, Pan Rye versus Director Joo)

1382
00:45:58,508 --> 00:45:59,747
Cham, cham, cham.

1383
00:45:59,748 --> 00:46:01,318
(Director Joo points to the right.)

1384
00:46:01,748 --> 00:46:03,517
(What could be the result?)

1385
00:46:03,518 --> 00:46:05,294
(In which direction did Pan Rye turn her head?)

1386
00:46:05,318 --> 00:46:06,687
Cham, cham, cham.

1387
00:46:06,688 --> 00:46:07,688
Yes!

1388
00:46:07,689 --> 00:46:08,887
Cham, cham, cham.

1389
00:46:08,888 --> 00:46:10,688
(She won again!)

1390
00:46:10,858 --> 00:46:12,057
I turned my head to the right.

1391
00:46:12,058 --> 00:46:13,058
(My sons get to eat now.)

1392
00:46:13,059 --> 00:46:14,727
- You did a great job.
- That means I won.

1393
00:46:14,728 --> 00:46:16,027
- You won.
- That's right.

1394
00:46:16,028 --> 00:46:17,128
(Director Joo lost again.)

1395
00:46:17,598 --> 00:46:20,298
(Ms. Kim, thank you.)

1396
00:46:20,338 --> 00:46:22,337
- We'll give them a plate.
- I hope they'll get a large plate.

1397
00:46:22,338 --> 00:46:23,738
I'm tearing up.

1398
00:46:23,938 --> 00:46:25,037
Give them a large plate.

1399
00:46:25,038 --> 00:46:26,878
I see there's a large plate behind you.

1400
00:46:27,078 --> 00:46:29,638
- Seon Ho, this is big enough.
- Okay. We can stack up the food.

1401
00:46:29,778 --> 00:46:31,077
Let's hurry up and eat before they take our food.

1402
00:46:31,078 --> 00:46:32,248
Come on, mister.

1403
00:46:32,448 --> 00:46:34,277
Instead of offering us some food,

1404
00:46:34,278 --> 00:46:35,947
you said, "Let's hurry up and eat before they take the food?"

1405
00:46:35,948 --> 00:46:37,424
(The food was so good that I blurted it out.)

1406
00:46:37,448 --> 00:46:39,988
- Seon Ho, that's messy.
- I did my best.

1407
00:46:40,718 --> 00:46:42,857
- You're spilling it everywhere.
- By the way...

1408
00:46:42,858 --> 00:46:43,858
(Joon says that Seon Ho's plate is messy.)

1409
00:46:43,859 --> 00:46:46,597
- Can't you...
- Oh, dear. Look at that.

1410
00:46:46,598 --> 00:46:48,257
- I'll have an octopus too.
- They're lucky to eat that much.

1411
00:46:48,258 --> 00:46:49,397
- You can't put food in here?
- No.

1412
00:46:49,398 --> 00:46:51,197
(DinDin even put an octopus on his plate.)

1413
00:46:51,198 --> 00:46:52,527
You can't have the broth?

1414
00:46:52,528 --> 00:46:54,097
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

1415
00:46:54,098 --> 00:46:55,368
- Dip it in this sauce.
- Okay.

1416
00:46:56,068 --> 00:46:57,068
We ate a lot.

1417
00:46:57,069 --> 00:46:59,307
- Thank you for this, Mom.
- No problem. Enjoy.

1418
00:46:59,308 --> 00:47:00,507
Oh, my. I can't stop eating this.

1419
00:47:00,508 --> 00:47:02,307
Ms. Kim, DinDin eats well now.

1420
00:47:02,308 --> 00:47:03,807
- Exactly.
- He eats a lot these days.

1421
00:47:03,808 --> 00:47:05,747
- I saw that he ate a lot.
- Ms. Kim, thank you for this.

1422
00:47:05,748 --> 00:47:07,518
Enjoy the food. Eat slowly.

1423
00:47:07,578 --> 00:47:09,217
Don't eat hastily.

1424
00:47:09,218 --> 00:47:10,317
(He tries the braised ribs that the older members praised.)

1425
00:47:10,318 --> 00:47:12,038
We're tortured with food every single week.

1426
00:47:13,158 --> 00:47:15,617
(The taste gets him excited.)

1427
00:47:15,618 --> 00:47:19,258
I learned how to make braised ribs from my mom.

1428
00:47:19,328 --> 00:47:20,997
- So I...
- It was when he was in Vancouver.

1429
00:47:20,998 --> 00:47:22,257
- I've been...
- You learned how to make this?

1430
00:47:22,258 --> 00:47:23,367
I've been making it by myself...

1431
00:47:23,368 --> 00:47:24,467
- since I was in Canada.
- He was in Canada.

1432
00:47:24,468 --> 00:47:25,468
- You can make this?
- Yes.

1433
00:47:25,469 --> 00:47:26,567
- And...
- Because he wants to eat it.

1434
00:47:26,568 --> 00:47:28,667
- I'm not lying.
- It tastes the same as mine.

1435
00:47:28,668 --> 00:47:30,407
No. My braised ribs tastes better than hers.

1436
00:47:30,408 --> 00:47:31,668
- Oh, come on.
- No way.

1437
00:47:31,738 --> 00:47:32,738
- Come on, you brat.
- It's true.

1438
00:47:32,739 --> 00:47:33,808
- No way.
- Nonsense.

1439
00:47:33,838 --> 00:47:35,758
- His sister said it was good.
- Just give me...

1440
00:47:35,878 --> 00:47:38,107
Just give me just three hours...

1441
00:47:38,108 --> 00:47:40,648
during a shoot later,

1442
00:47:40,748 --> 00:47:42,577
- and I'll make great braised ribs.
- He's good at it.

1443
00:47:42,578 --> 00:47:43,587
- Really?
- No way.

1444
00:47:43,588 --> 00:47:44,688
You just need three hours?

1445
00:47:44,918 --> 00:47:46,157
Yes, I just need three hours.

1446
00:47:46,158 --> 00:47:48,439
How about you wake up at 5am tomorrow and make it for us?

1447
00:47:49,928 --> 00:47:51,787
Since he brought it up, it's better to compare them right away.

1448
00:47:51,788 --> 00:47:52,857
That'd be the right way to see if it's true.

1449
00:47:52,858 --> 00:47:53,998
You can't outdo her.

1450
00:47:54,558 --> 00:47:55,718
It's impossible to outdo her.

1451
00:47:56,268 --> 00:47:59,198
(Seon Ho pours soy sauce marinated crab onto the rice.)

1452
00:47:59,668 --> 00:48:02,038
(He mixes it with the rice.)

1453
00:48:03,238 --> 00:48:07,578
(Then he starts gulping it down.)

1454
00:48:09,038 --> 00:48:11,607
(He's Mr. Five Meals a Day for a reason.)

1455
00:48:11,608 --> 00:48:12,677
- Ms. Kim, - That's right.

1456
00:48:12,678 --> 00:48:13,977
- I ate all the food that was here.
- Right.

1457
00:48:13,978 --> 00:48:15,247
- You saw how much food there was.
- Yes.

1458
00:48:15,248 --> 00:48:18,387
In fact, that's how servants used to eat in the past.

1459
00:48:18,388 --> 00:48:21,258
- Servants used to eat that much.
- That's right.

1460
00:48:21,718 --> 00:48:24,287
I'm impressed. Seon Ho eats a lot.

1461
00:48:24,288 --> 00:48:26,057
- Where does it all go?
- I don't know...

1462
00:48:26,058 --> 00:48:27,597
I said that before while watching the show.

1463
00:48:27,598 --> 00:48:28,897
I really don't know where it all goes.

1464
00:48:28,898 --> 00:48:32,228
This is the way of reacting that my mom wants to see.

1465
00:48:32,328 --> 00:48:35,467
- My family doesn't react this way.
- They don't say anything.

1466
00:48:35,468 --> 00:48:36,767
- I bet he's cynical.
- My gosh.

1467
00:48:36,768 --> 00:48:40,578
And then my two daughters post a photo of my food on social media.

1468
00:48:40,838 --> 00:48:42,278
"My mom's food."

1469
00:48:42,538 --> 00:48:45,178
"I feel resentful that I don't have a bigger stomach."

1470
00:48:45,248 --> 00:48:47,077
Your daughters express their gratitude on social media.

1471
00:48:47,078 --> 00:48:48,977
- They post it on social media.
- Daughters do it better than sons.

1472
00:48:48,978 --> 00:48:50,147
- Does Cheol not do it?
- You see...

1473
00:48:50,148 --> 00:48:53,088
Here's what comes to my mind lately.

1474
00:48:53,518 --> 00:48:55,258
Since my mom is on the older side,

1475
00:48:55,418 --> 00:48:56,857
I wonder how much more time I'll have...

1476
00:48:56,858 --> 00:48:58,027
- to enjoy her food.
- Right.

1477
00:48:58,028 --> 00:48:59,374
- That's been on my mind.
- Right.

1478
00:48:59,398 --> 00:49:01,127
So when she cooks for me,

1479
00:49:01,128 --> 00:49:02,628
I try to finish all the food.

1480
00:49:02,998 --> 00:49:04,127
I tell her that it's tasty.

1481
00:49:04,128 --> 00:49:05,444
(He's trying to express himself more.)

1482
00:49:05,468 --> 00:49:08,238
(Home-cooked meal, the best compliment DinDin can give)

1483
00:49:08,338 --> 00:49:10,368
- I finished my food.
- That's good.

1484
00:49:11,738 --> 00:49:12,937
Impressive. He finished his food.

1485
00:49:12,938 --> 00:49:15,907
- He got so much better.
- Indeed. He eats well now.

1486
00:49:15,908 --> 00:49:17,477
This is what we say at home.

1487
00:49:17,478 --> 00:49:19,617
"It must be that he's trying to survive on 2 Days 1 Night."

1488
00:49:19,618 --> 00:49:21,317
"Because they starve him on the show,"

1489
00:49:21,318 --> 00:49:22,677
- "he eats as much as he can..."
- That's right.

1490
00:49:22,678 --> 00:49:24,017
"when he has a chance."

1491
00:49:24,018 --> 00:49:25,247
(Cheol eats well thanks to 2 Days 1 Night.)

1492
00:49:25,248 --> 00:49:26,918
My husband and I think it's a good thing.

1493
00:49:26,958 --> 00:49:27,958
Do you want some sikhye?

1494
00:49:27,959 --> 00:49:30,227
- Oh, right.
- Sikhye sounds great.

1495
00:49:30,228 --> 00:49:31,287
Shake it.

1496
00:49:31,288 --> 00:49:33,457
This is a true delicacy. She made it all by herself at home.

1497
00:49:33,458 --> 00:49:35,497
Everything is so good that I don't want to move on to dessert.

1498
00:49:35,498 --> 00:49:37,538
(He doesn't want to move on to dessert yet, but...)

1499
00:49:37,828 --> 00:49:39,167
Let's all clank with sikhye...

1500
00:49:39,168 --> 00:49:42,067
for my mom's toast. And then we'll let her go.

1501
00:49:42,068 --> 00:49:44,238
- Okay.
- Ms. Kim, I really enjoyed it.

1502
00:49:44,268 --> 00:49:45,738
- It was so good.
- Thank you.

1503
00:49:45,868 --> 00:49:49,748
Everyone on the 2 Days 1 Night team, go for it.

1504
00:49:49,878 --> 00:49:51,647
And I hope...

1505
00:49:51,648 --> 00:49:55,648
your ratings will go up even higher this year.

1506
00:49:55,878 --> 00:49:57,617
To 2 Days 1 Night!

1507
00:49:57,618 --> 00:49:58,847
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

1508
00:49:58,848 --> 00:50:00,457
- Thank you for the food, Ms. Kim!
- Thank you.

1509
00:50:00,458 --> 00:50:02,357
- I wish you all good health.
- I really enjoyed the food.

1510
00:50:02,358 --> 00:50:04,557
- Thank you for the food.
- To Ms. Kim's health!

1511
00:50:04,558 --> 00:50:07,397
- Cheers!
- Thank you.

1512
00:50:07,398 --> 00:50:09,358
- Thank you.
- That was a good meal.

1513
00:50:09,868 --> 00:50:12,627
Ms. Kim, I will never forget your food.

1514
00:50:12,628 --> 00:50:14,737
- Did you honestly like my food?
- Yes, honestly.

1515
00:50:14,738 --> 00:50:17,067
- It was tasty.
- Please cook for us again.

1516
00:50:17,068 --> 00:50:18,407
I'll cook for you again.

1517
00:50:18,408 --> 00:50:20,978
I'll keep cooking for you guys as long as my health allows.

1518
00:50:21,038 --> 00:50:22,977
- I wish you good health.
- Thank you.

1519
00:50:22,978 --> 00:50:24,177
- I love you.
- Me too.

1520
00:50:24,178 --> 00:50:25,877
- Thank you, Mom.
- I hope to see you again soon.

1521
00:50:25,878 --> 00:50:26,878
See you later.

1522
00:50:27,048 --> 00:50:28,977
- Go home safely.
- Have a good evening.

1523
00:50:28,978 --> 00:50:30,917
- Goodbye.
- Give her a kiss, you brat.

1524
00:50:30,918 --> 00:50:32,038
Take a nap on your way home.

1525
00:50:32,118 --> 00:50:33,457
(Kissing)

1526
00:50:33,458 --> 00:50:34,857
- Take a nap on the way.
- Okay.

1527
00:50:34,858 --> 00:50:35,957
- Goodbye, Ms. Kim.
- Bye.

1528
00:50:35,958 --> 00:50:37,427
- Thank you for the food, Mom.
- Goodbye, Ms. Kim.

1529
00:50:37,428 --> 00:50:39,558
I didn't know that DinDin was a lovely son.

1530
00:50:39,728 --> 00:50:40,857
He's cute.

1531
00:50:40,858 --> 00:50:43,128
- Her food was good today.
- It was legendary.

1532
00:50:43,228 --> 00:50:44,897
He's so lucky he gets to enjoy such great food at home.

1533
00:50:44,898 --> 00:50:46,167
You're smart for a reason.

1534
00:50:46,168 --> 00:50:48,267
("The number of best foods equals that of all mothers in the world.")

1535
00:50:48,268 --> 00:50:50,368
(From Huh Young Man's "Sikgaek")

1536
00:50:50,908 --> 00:50:52,407
Oh, my. I feel so full and energetic.

1537
00:50:52,408 --> 00:50:54,107
- Is that our tent?
- What's that?

1538
00:50:54,108 --> 00:50:55,308
- What?
- It looks quite nice.

1539
00:50:55,678 --> 00:50:56,808
Is it for us?

1540
00:50:56,878 --> 00:50:58,948
I see number 4. Where are the numbers 1 to 3?

1541
00:50:59,408 --> 00:51:00,877
- What?
- What's going on?

1542
00:51:00,878 --> 00:51:02,077
There's number 1 there. And number 2 and number 3.

1543
00:51:02,078 --> 00:51:03,558
Where's number three? I don't see it.

1544
00:51:03,988 --> 00:51:07,018
Do you remember the theme of our trip?

1545
00:51:07,758 --> 00:51:09,557
(Lying on the Incheon Seashore)

1546
00:51:09,558 --> 00:51:10,687
- That was it, right?
- Yes.

1547
00:51:10,688 --> 00:51:12,387
You've worked so hard today...

1548
00:51:12,388 --> 00:51:14,898
for a good night's sleep outdoors by the Incheon Sea.

1549
00:51:15,528 --> 00:51:17,197
The number of the members to sleep outdoors...

1550
00:51:17,198 --> 00:51:19,567
that was decided after fierce competition is...

1551
00:51:19,568 --> 00:51:20,667
- Three.
- Three.

1552
00:51:20,668 --> 00:51:21,767
Three.

1553
00:51:21,768 --> 00:51:25,238
Today's Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors that will determine...

1554
00:51:25,538 --> 00:51:27,378
the members to sleep outdoors is...

1555
00:51:27,408 --> 00:51:31,077
- Room Mafia in the Middle of Night.
- Room Mafia in the Middle of Night?

1556
00:51:31,078 --> 00:51:32,248
Is it like the mafia game?

1557
00:51:32,608 --> 00:51:34,178
If you look over there,

1558
00:51:34,548 --> 00:51:36,248
- you'll see numbers 1 and 2.
- Yes.

1559
00:51:37,388 --> 00:51:40,218
(There are two separate rooms inside.)

1560
00:51:40,288 --> 00:51:42,857
Look up, and you'll see number 3 on the 3rd floor.

1561
00:51:42,858 --> 00:51:43,987
(There's Room 3 on the 3rd floor.)

1562
00:51:43,988 --> 00:51:45,357
Look behind you, and you'll see number four.

1563
00:51:45,358 --> 00:51:46,358
(The tent in the yard is Room 4.)

1564
00:51:46,359 --> 00:51:48,558
- On its left is Room Five.
- Okay.

1565
00:51:49,498 --> 00:51:50,697
(Room 5, Room 4, Room 1, Room 2, Room 3)

1566
00:51:50,698 --> 00:51:52,397
(There are five rooms in total.)

1567
00:51:52,398 --> 00:51:53,537
- You can see them, right?
- Yes.

1568
00:51:53,538 --> 00:51:55,497
Among the five rooms,

1569
00:51:55,498 --> 00:51:56,837
(There are five rooms in total.)

1570
00:51:56,838 --> 00:51:58,684
two of them have a sign that says, "sleep indoors..."

1571
00:51:58,708 --> 00:52:01,137
while the other three have a sign that says, "sleep outdoors."

1572
00:52:01,138 --> 00:52:02,177
(Three rooms are marked "sleep outdoors.")

1573
00:52:02,178 --> 00:52:04,948
You will randomly choose a room.

1574
00:52:05,608 --> 00:52:07,878
After that, through four different games,

1575
00:52:07,978 --> 00:52:11,948
the winner of each game will switch rooms with the member of his choice.

1576
00:52:12,248 --> 00:52:14,364
Can I choose not to switch rooms if I'm to sleep indoors?

1577
00:52:14,388 --> 00:52:16,427
- When you place first, - The winner must switch rooms?

1578
00:52:16,428 --> 00:52:18,527
You must switch rooms no matter what.

1579
00:52:18,528 --> 00:52:19,874
- Understood.
- When I place first?

1580
00:52:19,898 --> 00:52:22,128
Correct. After all the games end,

1581
00:52:22,558 --> 00:52:24,727
if the room you're assigned...

1582
00:52:24,728 --> 00:52:26,867
has a "sleep indoors" sign, he gets to sleep indoors.

1583
00:52:26,868 --> 00:52:28,397
- Okay.
- You choose a room.

1584
00:52:28,398 --> 00:52:29,907
When you enter the room, you'll find out your destiny.

1585
00:52:29,908 --> 00:52:31,507
But you won't tell the others like in the mafia game.

1586
00:52:31,508 --> 00:52:33,307
If you want to switch rooms to change your destiny,

1587
00:52:33,308 --> 00:52:36,037
- You need to win a game.
- you should win a game.

1588
00:52:36,038 --> 00:52:37,624
- Oh, I see. It's easy.
- You just have to lose.

1589
00:52:37,648 --> 00:52:39,917
- That's how this game works.
- Losing can be a strategy too.

1590
00:52:39,918 --> 00:52:42,194
- Right. If I'm to sleep indoors, - Without letting the others know.

1591
00:52:42,218 --> 00:52:43,487
- I'd try to lose in a game.
- You lose intentionally.

1592
00:52:43,488 --> 00:52:45,187
I see. That's how this works.

1593
00:52:45,188 --> 00:52:46,217
(The key is to read one another's mind and deceive the others.)

1594
00:52:46,218 --> 00:52:47,587
All right. Good. It sounds fun.

1595
00:52:47,588 --> 00:52:49,357
In my opinion,

1596
00:52:49,358 --> 00:52:52,457
DinDin is at an advantage in this game as he's smart.

1597
00:52:52,458 --> 00:52:54,857
DinDin and Jong Min are at an advantage.

1598
00:52:54,858 --> 00:52:57,198
- That's right.
- Joon is an open book.

1599
00:52:57,268 --> 00:52:58,527
I don't think Seon Ho will do well.

1600
00:52:58,528 --> 00:53:00,314
(He thinks Seon Ho won't do well for no reason.)

1601
00:53:00,338 --> 00:53:01,467
Come on, Se Yoon.

1602
00:53:01,468 --> 00:53:02,597
How could you say such a thing about me?

1603
00:53:02,598 --> 00:53:03,607
- Statistically speaking, I mean.
- I see.

1604
00:53:03,608 --> 00:53:04,938
Yes, I analyzed the statistics.

1605
00:53:05,568 --> 00:53:06,977
- Now...
- Our destiny will be decided.

1606
00:53:06,978 --> 00:53:09,177
- Choose the first room.
- Choosing a room isn't important.

1607
00:53:09,178 --> 00:53:11,908
- The games are important.
- Here you go.

1608
00:53:12,008 --> 00:53:13,118
Pick one.

1609
00:53:13,818 --> 00:53:15,047
Pick one.

1610
00:53:15,048 --> 00:53:16,917
- I'll choose my own destiny.
- Why am I the last to choose?

1611
00:53:16,918 --> 00:53:18,087
- Pick one.
- Wait for your turn.

1612
00:53:18,088 --> 00:53:19,248
I must choose my own destiny.

1613
00:53:19,348 --> 00:53:20,518
Pick one.

1614
00:53:21,858 --> 00:53:22,887
The last one.

1615
00:53:22,888 --> 00:53:24,457
Choosing a room is not really important.

1616
00:53:24,458 --> 00:53:25,957
- It's not important.
- I picked Room One.

1617
00:53:25,958 --> 00:53:27,057
(Room 1, Moon Se Yoon)

1618
00:53:27,058 --> 00:53:28,257
- I picked Room 2.
- You picked Room 2?

1619
00:53:28,258 --> 00:53:29,297
(Room 2, Kim Jong Min)

1620
00:53:29,298 --> 00:53:30,968
- I picked Room 3.
- Room 5.

1621
00:53:31,628 --> 00:53:32,698
Now...

1622
00:53:33,198 --> 00:53:34,997
You can go to the rooms that you just picked.

1623
00:53:34,998 --> 00:53:36,837
Find out where you'll be sleeping.

1624
00:53:36,838 --> 00:53:38,207
- Okay.
- Let's go.

1625
00:53:38,208 --> 00:53:39,368
All right, DinDin...

1626
00:53:40,738 --> 00:53:42,737
He picked number five.

1627
00:53:42,738 --> 00:53:43,884
(Keeping Brain DinDin in check)

1628
00:53:43,908 --> 00:53:46,448
(DinDin also keeps them in check.)

1629
00:53:46,618 --> 00:53:48,847
Goodness, Seon Ho is going up.

1630
00:53:48,848 --> 00:53:49,848
I'm going up.

1631
00:53:49,848 --> 00:53:50,848
(Seon Ho is going up to the 3rd floor.)

1632
00:53:50,849 --> 00:53:52,287
You can't see mine.

1633
00:53:52,288 --> 00:53:53,457
I won't.

1634
00:53:53,458 --> 00:53:54,488
(Room 1, Room 2)

1635
00:53:55,718 --> 00:53:57,788
- I picked number one.
- Right.

1636
00:53:58,828 --> 00:53:59,928
I picked Room One.

1637
00:54:00,398 --> 00:54:02,657
- I picked this room.
- All right, goodness.

1638
00:54:02,658 --> 00:54:03,698
Good catch.

1639
00:54:05,528 --> 00:54:06,637
(Knocking)

1640
00:54:06,638 --> 00:54:07,698
Anyone there?

1641
00:54:07,968 --> 00:54:09,468
Anyone sleeping indoors?

1642
00:54:11,338 --> 00:54:13,378
(The cue card placed right in front of him)

1643
00:54:13,778 --> 00:54:17,978
(The cue card reveals the room's identity.)

1644
00:54:18,408 --> 00:54:20,318
(Please let me sleep indoors.)

1645
00:54:26,618 --> 00:54:29,018
(Awkward reactions from the members after the reveal)

1646
00:54:29,388 --> 00:54:30,458
Did you see it?

1647
00:54:31,188 --> 00:54:32,188
Let me flip it.

1648
00:54:38,798 --> 00:54:42,468
(A room so bad it makes him want to cry?)

1649
00:54:43,168 --> 00:54:46,808
(Screaming)

1650
00:54:47,808 --> 00:54:48,808
He's screaming.

1651
00:54:48,808 --> 00:54:49,808
(The man next door is so noisy.)

1652
00:54:49,808 --> 00:54:50,808
That man...

1653
00:54:52,148 --> 00:54:53,248
He's screaming.

1654
00:54:55,848 --> 00:54:57,118
(Please keep quiet.)

1655
00:54:57,148 --> 00:54:58,648
(He scared me.)

1656
00:54:59,148 --> 00:55:02,818
(Keeping each other in check while screaming)

1657
00:55:03,158 --> 00:55:05,457
(What's happening?)

1658
00:55:05,458 --> 00:55:06,938
Which room will let me sleep indoors?

1659
00:55:07,098 --> 00:55:08,227
Just tell me.

1660
00:55:08,228 --> 00:55:09,228
(Asking the production crew for the information)

1661
00:55:09,229 --> 00:55:10,527
My mom is out of reach.

1662
00:55:10,528 --> 00:55:12,097
(Even bringing his mom into this?)

1663
00:55:12,098 --> 00:55:14,538
My mom is out of reach.

1664
00:55:14,568 --> 00:55:16,737
I haven't heard from her since she got on the car.

1665
00:55:16,738 --> 00:55:18,298
(Safely escorting DinDin's mother home)

1666
00:55:19,008 --> 00:55:23,708
(Which room will let them sleep indoors?)

1667
00:55:25,008 --> 00:55:26,147
My goodness.

1668
00:55:26,148 --> 00:55:27,177
(The mind game begins the moment they step outside.)

1669
00:55:27,178 --> 00:55:28,217
(Will Jong Min sleep indoors? Will Se Yoon sleep indoors?)

1670
00:55:28,218 --> 00:55:29,848
- Aren't you having fun?
- My goodness.

1671
00:55:30,848 --> 00:55:33,218
(Is Seon Ho sleeping indoors?)

1672
00:55:35,318 --> 00:55:36,458
They're still not here.

1673
00:55:36,828 --> 00:55:38,628
(Is Joon sleeping indoors?)

1674
00:55:40,628 --> 00:55:41,628
(Is DinDin sleeping indoors?)

1675
00:55:41,629 --> 00:55:42,798
Everyone, gather up.

1676
00:55:43,998 --> 00:55:44,998
(Only two of them get to sleep indoors.)

1677
00:55:44,999 --> 00:55:46,959
- Why are you all smiling?
- Let's play the game!

1678
00:55:47,068 --> 00:55:48,098
Why are you all smiling?

1679
00:55:49,238 --> 00:55:50,968
They are all smiling.

1680
00:55:51,338 --> 00:55:52,407
Let's start the game.

1681
00:55:52,408 --> 00:55:53,438
What's wrong with him?

1682
00:55:53,678 --> 00:55:54,678
This is strange.

1683
00:55:55,338 --> 00:55:57,658
- Let's play it fair and square.
- What's up with you all?

1684
00:55:57,948 --> 00:55:59,247
(Keeping a poker face)

1685
00:55:59,248 --> 00:56:00,947
- What?
- You can ask those questions?

1686
00:56:00,948 --> 00:56:02,347
(Every moment becomes a clue.)

1687
00:56:02,348 --> 00:56:05,687
We just need to see who tries the hardest in this game.

1688
00:56:05,688 --> 00:56:06,717
- Right - Yes.

1689
00:56:06,718 --> 00:56:08,598
- You don't need to ask.
- All right, everyone.

1690
00:56:09,258 --> 00:56:12,627
As shared, the winner has to switch rooms...

1691
00:56:12,628 --> 00:56:14,357
- whether he wants it or not.
- Okay.

1692
00:56:14,358 --> 00:56:15,827
The rest of us have no other choice.

1693
00:56:15,828 --> 00:56:16,927
That's right.

1694
00:56:16,928 --> 00:56:18,168
The first game is...

1695
00:56:18,798 --> 00:56:20,998
Relay Times Table Game.

1696
00:56:21,468 --> 00:56:24,307
- We'll do a relay times table game.
- Okay.

1697
00:56:24,308 --> 00:56:26,537
If you get it wrong, we move on to the next person.

1698
00:56:26,538 --> 00:56:27,807
Then the round continues.

1699
00:56:27,808 --> 00:56:28,808
- All right.
- Okay.

1700
00:56:28,809 --> 00:56:30,107
Whoever lasts until the end...

1701
00:56:30,108 --> 00:56:32,408
- Hold on.
- Two times two is four.

1702
00:56:32,548 --> 00:56:35,348
They are so bad at this. How will you pick the winner?

1703
00:56:35,878 --> 00:56:36,988
What do you mean by "they?"

1704
00:56:37,048 --> 00:56:39,347
- Joon is horrible at this.
- Well, 6 times 7 is 32.

1705
00:56:39,348 --> 00:56:40,387
And 6 times 8 is 36.

1706
00:56:40,388 --> 00:56:41,558
What, 6 times 8 is 36?

1707
00:56:41,888 --> 00:56:43,118
