2472
01:24:07,810 --> 01:24:09,409
(The one who takes the most photos of the members' faces goes home.)

2473
01:24:09,410 --> 01:24:11,850
We should find a camera and take photos of the members?

2474
01:24:12,280 --> 01:24:14,426
(It counts only when the face is bigger than a penny coin.)

2475
01:24:14,450 --> 01:24:15,450
Where do we go?

2476
01:24:15,451 --> 01:24:17,096
(It's okay to take a photo of the face sticker they're wearing.)

2477
01:24:17,120 --> 01:24:19,760
(Only 1 person can go home right away.)

2478
01:24:20,660 --> 01:24:24,660
(They run around frantically as soon as they get up.)

2479
01:24:29,130 --> 01:24:31,839
Everyone, you must keep taking photos for five minutes.

2480
01:24:31,840 --> 01:24:34,340
We will check the photos when the five minutes are up.

2481
01:24:35,070 --> 01:24:36,140
Take off the hood.

2482
01:24:36,470 --> 01:24:39,579
The cameras are hidden in different places.

2483
01:24:39,580 --> 01:24:42,880
It doesn't count if the photo doesn't have a face, right?

2484
01:24:44,620 --> 01:24:46,479
(It's quite difficult to take accurate photos with a Polaroid.)

2485
01:24:46,480 --> 01:24:47,820
I'm dizzy.

2486
01:24:49,020 --> 01:24:51,189
It has to be bigger than a penny coin.

2487
01:24:51,190 --> 01:24:52,496
(It's hard to take a photo of the headbanging ninja.)

2488
01:24:52,520 --> 01:24:53,520
(He attacks and defends at the same time.)

2489
01:24:53,521 --> 01:24:54,690
This is killing me.

2490
01:24:55,530 --> 01:24:57,400
(The thorough mollusk, Joon)

2491
01:24:58,560 --> 01:24:59,829
Don't take a photo of me.

2492
01:24:59,830 --> 01:25:00,900
Why not?

2493
01:25:01,030 --> 01:25:02,230
I have to attend a wedding.

2494
01:25:02,470 --> 01:25:03,670
(What is he talking about?)

2495
01:25:04,440 --> 01:25:06,039
It should be bigger than a penny coin.

2496
01:25:06,040 --> 01:25:07,140
Take off the hood.

2497
01:25:07,870 --> 01:25:10,810
(Desperate headbanging)

2498
01:25:11,480 --> 01:25:13,280
(Then he chases Se Yoon!)

2499
01:25:13,880 --> 01:25:16,750
(His photography skills are terrible.)

2500
01:25:16,980 --> 01:25:18,920
The photo of the sticker also counts, right?

2501
01:25:19,080 --> 01:25:20,720
(By the way, where's Jong Min?)

2502
01:25:20,920 --> 01:25:23,790
(He just got up.)

2503
01:25:24,690 --> 01:25:25,920
(Jong Min)

2504
01:25:26,290 --> 01:25:28,690
(He sneaks a peak hiding next to a building.)

2505
01:25:29,530 --> 01:25:31,260
(Stealthy)

2506
01:25:31,660 --> 01:25:32,860
(Looking for a camera)

2507
01:25:34,770 --> 01:25:36,570
(I got you, lazy old man.)

2508
01:25:39,570 --> 01:25:41,170
(DinDin gets a decent shot.)

2509
01:25:41,410 --> 01:25:43,270
(Looking around half-asleep)

2510
01:25:45,580 --> 01:25:46,680
It's so hard.

2511
01:25:49,250 --> 01:25:50,850
(This time, he quickly defends.)

2512
01:25:50,880 --> 01:25:52,049
I'm tired.

2513
01:25:52,050 --> 01:25:53,930
(He takes photos of the members a little late.)

2514
01:25:54,250 --> 01:25:56,350
(You have to take photos of their faces.)

2515
01:25:56,590 --> 01:25:58,360
(He doesn't understand the rules.)

2516
01:25:59,920 --> 01:26:02,260
(They aim at Jong Min's back.)

2517
01:26:02,760 --> 01:26:04,130
(I'm going after DinDin.)

2518
01:26:04,260 --> 01:26:06,580
(They take photos of each other while being photographed.)

2519
01:26:07,470 --> 01:26:09,130
(He's out of film.)

2520
01:26:09,700 --> 01:26:11,500
(Come here, Lee Joon.)

2521
01:26:11,840 --> 01:26:14,310
The face has to be bigger than a 50-won coin.

2522
01:26:16,170 --> 01:26:17,510
I'm feeling ashamed.

2523
01:26:18,210 --> 01:26:20,850
(His head feels ashamed, but his body doesn't stop.)

2524
01:26:20,950 --> 01:26:22,210
One minute left.

2525
01:26:22,610 --> 01:26:24,956
(At this moment, there's a man standing right in the center.)

2526
01:26:24,980 --> 01:26:27,750
(He just takes landscape photos and doesn't avoid others.)

2527
01:26:28,250 --> 01:26:29,550
(Spotting the prey)

2528
01:26:30,320 --> 01:26:31,820
(He fails even when it's so easy.)

2529
01:26:32,090 --> 01:26:33,850
(Seon Ho found a good place to take photos.)

2530
01:26:34,090 --> 01:26:35,730
Jong Min, you should run away.

2531
01:26:37,460 --> 01:26:40,230
- I'm feeling dizzy.
- Don't do that.

2532
01:26:42,100 --> 01:26:43,400
It's so hard.

2533
01:26:43,530 --> 01:26:45,170
Five, four,

2534
01:26:45,500 --> 01:26:48,110
three, two, one.

2535
01:26:48,370 --> 01:26:51,109
Time's up. Put down the cameras.

2536
01:26:51,110 --> 01:26:52,140
(Time's up.)

2537
01:26:52,610 --> 01:26:55,109
- I'll announce the results.
- Tell us the rankings.

2538
01:26:55,110 --> 01:26:56,509
- What? The rankings?
- The rankings.

2539
01:26:56,510 --> 01:26:58,349
- Start with the 5th.
- The 5th place?

2540
01:26:58,350 --> 01:26:59,350
- Yes.
- Yes.

2541
01:26:59,420 --> 01:27:00,450
Lee Joon.

2542
01:27:00,790 --> 01:27:01,820
You got nothing?

2543
01:27:02,190 --> 01:27:04,419
He tried the hardest, though.

2544
01:27:04,420 --> 01:27:06,859
Do you even know how expensive the film is?

2545
01:27:06,860 --> 01:27:08,140
(Unfortunate photography skills)

2546
01:27:09,090 --> 01:27:10,630
- All right.
- I tried really hard.

2547
01:27:10,800 --> 01:27:12,430
The fourth place is Se Yoon.

2548
01:27:12,460 --> 01:27:13,970
- That's perfect.
- One photo.

2549
01:27:14,070 --> 01:27:15,070
The third.

2550
01:27:15,730 --> 01:27:16,730
Seon Ho.

2551
01:27:17,470 --> 01:27:19,369
- My goodness.
- Seon Ho.

2552
01:27:19,370 --> 01:27:20,370
Why?

2553
01:27:20,370 --> 01:27:21,370
(His rival is out.)

2554
01:27:21,570 --> 01:27:22,969
- He got two.
- What?

2555
01:27:22,970 --> 01:27:25,710
- Why?
- It should be bigger than a coin.

2556
01:27:26,010 --> 01:27:28,180
Hang on. Jong Min took more than two photos?

2557
01:27:28,580 --> 01:27:30,920
- Of course.
- You stood there doing nothing.

2558
01:27:30,950 --> 01:27:32,380
I have my skills.

2559
01:27:32,450 --> 01:27:33,480
All right.

2560
01:27:33,620 --> 01:27:35,020
(Seriously, what's with him?)

2561
01:27:36,390 --> 01:27:39,190
The winner of Incredible Moment, Spotting Face.

2562
01:27:39,460 --> 01:27:42,259
The one photographed by the paparazzi, or not?

2563
01:27:42,260 --> 01:27:43,630
- All right.
- The winner is...

2564
01:27:44,060 --> 01:27:45,460
(Jong Min?)

2565
01:27:46,530 --> 01:27:47,530
DinDin.

2566
01:27:48,030 --> 01:27:49,099
Is it DinDin?

2567
01:27:49,100 --> 01:27:50,669
(The winner, DinDin, gets to go home.)

2568
01:27:50,670 --> 01:27:52,940
My goodness. Show us your front teeth.

2569
01:27:53,570 --> 01:27:54,640
Okay.

2570
01:27:55,240 --> 01:27:57,110
(Showing Sonny's camera celebration in joy)

2571
01:27:58,610 --> 01:28:01,050
- You can't stop me from going home.
- How many did they get?

2572
01:28:01,750 --> 01:28:02,750
Four.

2573
01:28:02,910 --> 01:28:04,020
He took a lot.

2574
01:28:04,250 --> 01:28:05,620
He took that many photos?

2575
01:28:06,020 --> 01:28:07,020
Just once.

2576
01:28:07,021 --> 01:28:11,990
(He took photos of the members who approached him.)

2577
01:28:12,720 --> 01:28:14,029
(This is my skill.)

2578
01:28:14,030 --> 01:28:15,530
And DinDin...

2579
01:28:15,890 --> 01:28:18,159
- He took 8 photos?
- took 7 photos.

2580
01:28:18,160 --> 01:28:19,629
Really? That's a lot.

2581
01:28:19,630 --> 01:28:20,669
It's a big difference.

2582
01:28:20,670 --> 01:28:21,899
(DinDin took good photos with big faces.)

2583
01:28:21,900 --> 01:28:24,469
DinDin gets to go home.

2584
01:28:24,470 --> 01:28:26,670
- Right away? I'm jealous.
- Thank you.

2585
01:28:26,900 --> 01:28:28,339
- Everyone.
- Yes?

2586
01:28:28,340 --> 01:28:29,469
(Everyone?)

2587
01:28:29,470 --> 01:28:32,739
We will have one more person go home.

2588
01:28:32,740 --> 01:28:33,740
Okay.

2589
01:28:34,080 --> 01:28:36,580
- What? There's a plane?
- What's that?

2590
01:28:37,050 --> 01:28:38,080
What?

2591
01:28:38,620 --> 01:28:41,749
The first one to get the Getting-off-work Ticket can go.

2592
01:28:41,750 --> 01:28:42,820
- Really?
- Seriously?

2593
01:28:44,790 --> 01:28:46,260
Pick it up after it falls.

2594
01:28:46,660 --> 01:28:48,290
You might get hurt.

2595
01:28:48,930 --> 01:28:50,290
Gosh, seriously...

2596
01:28:50,530 --> 01:28:52,930
(In the end, of the two faster ones, )

2597
01:28:53,330 --> 01:28:56,200
(Seon Ho won the Getting-off-work Ticket.)

2598
01:28:56,300 --> 01:29:00,669
Jong Min, Se Yoon, and Joon, who lost the games,

2599
01:29:00,670 --> 01:29:01,670
Yes?

2600
01:29:01,671 --> 01:29:04,440
Will head to the Eurwangni Beach in Incheon,

2601
01:29:04,980 --> 01:29:07,210
gather citizens at the beach,

2602
01:29:07,650 --> 01:29:10,209
and perform an impromptu busking...

2603
01:29:10,210 --> 01:29:11,619
before going home.

2604
01:29:11,620 --> 01:29:14,089
That's a tough one.

2605
01:29:14,090 --> 01:29:16,989
Are there people at Eurwangni Beach at this hour?

2606
01:29:16,990 --> 01:29:18,490
There's no one around this time.

2607
01:29:19,060 --> 01:29:20,629
(At that time, Eurwangni Beach)

2608
01:29:20,630 --> 01:29:22,690
(It's quiet and nice.)

2609
01:29:22,860 --> 01:29:25,029
We will see you on our next trip. Thank you.

2610
01:29:25,030 --> 01:29:26,260
(Sad)

2611
01:29:27,030 --> 01:29:29,870
(Heading to Eurwangni Beach for busking)

2612
01:29:30,270 --> 01:29:32,740
We can do it like "Begin Again."

2613
01:29:32,840 --> 01:29:34,509
- "Begin Again?"
- Like "Begin Again."

2614
01:29:34,510 --> 01:29:35,570
Let's do this.

2615
01:29:35,740 --> 01:29:36,740
All right.

2616
01:29:37,110 --> 01:29:39,980
But there's no one around this time.

2617
01:29:40,110 --> 01:29:42,030
Why would people come to Eurwangni at this hour?

2618
01:29:42,410 --> 01:29:43,579
If there are a few people...

2619
01:29:43,580 --> 01:29:45,479
We can perform even if there's only one person.

2620
01:29:45,480 --> 01:29:48,090
People will probably gather if you work out topless there.

2621
01:29:49,250 --> 01:29:50,719
- It's like nude busking.
- Nude busking.

2622
01:29:50,720 --> 01:29:52,459
- Nude busking.
- Nude busking?

2623
01:29:52,460 --> 01:29:53,719
You should do that.

2624
01:29:53,720 --> 01:29:55,080
- I just take off my shirt?
- Yes.

2625
01:29:56,430 --> 01:29:58,429
It's Eurwangni.

2626
01:29:58,430 --> 01:30:00,990
(They arrive at the destination before deciding on the setlist.)

2627
01:30:01,100 --> 01:30:03,570
(A very foggy early morning)

2628
01:30:04,270 --> 01:30:07,200
(There is not a single person passing by.)

2629
01:30:08,010 --> 01:30:09,570
We should at least gather the seagulls.

2630
01:30:09,640 --> 01:30:12,210
(They will have to gather the seagulls instead.)

2631
01:30:12,910 --> 01:30:15,280
Our goal is to gather ten people.

2632
01:30:16,080 --> 01:30:18,120
(But we're alone here.)

2633
01:30:18,150 --> 01:30:20,280
- Let's have ten seats ready first.
- Okay.

2634
01:30:20,480 --> 01:30:21,890
(They set up the seats first.)

2635
01:30:22,450 --> 01:30:24,819
(The members set up everything themselves.)

2636
01:30:24,820 --> 01:30:26,020
Ten seats.

2637
01:30:27,190 --> 01:30:28,190
(Now all that's left is to gather 10 people.)

2638
01:30:28,191 --> 01:30:32,300
The members of 2 Days 1 Night are busking now.

2639
01:30:32,960 --> 01:30:34,170
(Embarrassed)

2640
01:30:34,270 --> 01:30:35,869
We're busking. We only accept ten people.

2641
01:30:35,870 --> 01:30:37,500
It's almost full.

2642
01:30:37,900 --> 01:30:40,239
- There's no one, and it's full?
- Yes.

2643
01:30:40,240 --> 01:30:41,670
Are we this unpopular?

2644
01:30:42,440 --> 01:30:43,470
No one's coming.

2645
01:30:43,810 --> 01:30:45,179
Hello.

2646
01:30:45,180 --> 01:30:47,140
- Hello.
- All right.

2647
01:30:47,210 --> 01:30:49,149
(Thankfully, people are coming to see them.)

2648
01:30:49,150 --> 01:30:50,349
Hello.

2649
01:30:50,350 --> 01:30:51,520
2 Days!

2650
01:30:51,750 --> 01:30:53,620
- 1 Night!
- Yes!

2651
01:30:53,780 --> 01:30:55,926
This is a free busking performance. Nice to meet you. Please come.

2652
01:30:55,950 --> 01:30:58,059
Please come, everyone.

2653
01:30:58,060 --> 01:30:59,720
(They have 4 people in the audience.)

2654
01:30:59,960 --> 01:31:01,129
- Come over here.
- Come here.

2655
01:31:01,130 --> 01:31:02,459
Hurry. It's okay.

2656
01:31:02,460 --> 01:31:03,559
Joon. Go there...

2657
01:31:03,560 --> 01:31:05,059
- and tell them to come.
- Joon, you should go.

2658
01:31:05,060 --> 01:31:07,399
He's coming to capture the hearts of women.

2659
01:31:07,400 --> 01:31:08,800
Two people are coming.

2660
01:31:08,970 --> 01:31:10,299
This is a hand warmer. It's cold, right?

2661
01:31:10,300 --> 01:31:11,780
Here. These are hand warmers for you.

2662
01:31:11,840 --> 01:31:14,969
- They're here to see Joon.
- Today...

2663
01:31:14,970 --> 01:31:17,069
- She got it.
- It's full.

2664
01:31:17,070 --> 01:31:19,009
- It's full now.
- All seats are taken.

2665
01:31:19,010 --> 01:31:22,209
All right. We'll have a brief chat with the audience.

2666
01:31:22,210 --> 01:31:23,279
Please ask them...

2667
01:31:23,280 --> 01:31:24,579
- where they're from.
- Okay.

2668
01:31:24,580 --> 01:31:26,449
Who do you think you came the furthest from here?

2669
01:31:26,450 --> 01:31:27,619
Who came the furthest from here?

2670
01:31:27,620 --> 01:31:28,919
Where are you from?

2671
01:31:28,920 --> 01:31:30,019
Gwangju Metropolitan City.

2672
01:31:30,020 --> 01:31:31,859
- Gwangju Metropolitan City!
- Gwangju!

2673
01:31:31,860 --> 01:31:34,460
Nice to meet you. Raise your hand if you came even farther.

2674
01:31:34,590 --> 01:31:36,089
You in the back.

2675
01:31:36,090 --> 01:31:38,459
- Sir. Where are you from?
- Which region?

2676
01:31:38,460 --> 01:31:39,460
Vietnam.

2677
01:31:39,461 --> 01:31:40,970
- Vietnam?
- Vietnam!

2678
01:31:41,030 --> 01:31:43,100
(What? Vietnam?)

2679
01:31:43,870 --> 01:31:46,039
- Ho Chi Minh!
- Xin chao!

2680
01:31:46,040 --> 01:31:47,276
(The man came from really far away.)

2681
01:31:47,300 --> 01:31:49,140
Anyone who came from farther than Vietnam?

2682
01:31:49,540 --> 01:31:51,380
- Where is...
- Where are you from?

2683
01:31:52,010 --> 01:31:53,309
Cheongsan Island.

2684
01:31:53,310 --> 01:31:54,786
- Cheongsan Island?
- Cheongsan Island?

2685
01:31:54,810 --> 01:31:57,049
Maybe you don't know where Vietnam is.

2686
01:31:57,050 --> 01:31:58,456
(The lady from Cheongsan Island is full of humor.)

2687
01:31:58,480 --> 01:32:00,150
(It makes everyone laugh.)

2688
01:32:00,220 --> 01:32:01,989
- We...
- 2 Days 1 Night went there a lot.

2689
01:32:01,990 --> 01:32:03,519
- Yes.
- That's true.

2690
01:32:03,520 --> 01:32:05,089
We're a little embarrassed now...

2691
01:32:05,090 --> 01:32:07,389
since we are busking, which wasn't planned.

2692
01:32:07,390 --> 01:32:09,729
We will take some song requests.

2693
01:32:09,730 --> 01:32:11,399
Is there a song you'd like to listen to?

2694
01:32:11,400 --> 01:32:13,259
- "Amor Fati."
- Pardon?

2695
01:32:13,260 --> 01:32:15,429
- "Amor Fati?"
- "Amor Fati?"

2696
01:32:15,430 --> 01:32:17,369
We will end today's memories...

2697
01:32:17,370 --> 01:32:20,339
with "Amor Fati" at Eurwangni.

2698
01:32:20,340 --> 01:32:23,840
- Yes! "Amor Fati!"
- "Amor Fati!"

2699
01:32:24,010 --> 01:32:25,910
(Dancing)

2700
01:32:26,340 --> 01:32:27,849
(Joon takes the center of the stage.)

2701
01:32:27,850 --> 01:32:29,710
- They're starting to get up.
- Ma'am.

2702
01:32:30,310 --> 01:32:31,320
Stand up.

2703
01:32:37,890 --> 01:32:38,920
Come over here!

2704
01:32:39,120 --> 01:32:40,790
Yes, that's it. Nice.

2705
01:32:40,990 --> 01:32:42,060
Stand up!

2706
01:32:43,160 --> 01:32:46,200
(Life begins now)

2707
01:32:46,930 --> 01:32:48,770
Let's go!

2708
01:32:48,900 --> 01:32:50,470
(A mistake)

2709
01:32:50,500 --> 01:32:52,199
- Amor fati - Let's go!

2710
01:32:52,200 --> 01:32:55,170
(Amor fati)

2711
01:32:55,610 --> 01:33:00,310
(In a trance)

2712
01:33:00,380 --> 01:33:03,109
- Girls, stand up too.
- On your feet, everyone!

2713
01:33:03,110 --> 01:33:04,920
- Join us.
- Come on over!

2714
01:33:04,950 --> 01:33:07,649
- Amor fati.
- Come here, ma'am.

2715
01:33:07,650 --> 01:33:09,690
(Thanks for cheering with us early in the morning.)

2716
01:33:10,090 --> 01:33:12,520
- Oh, my.
- Amor Fati

2717
01:33:13,020 --> 01:33:14,890
(Next episode)

2718
01:33:16,260 --> 01:33:20,830
(Back to the 90s in Cheongdo)

2719
01:33:23,600 --> 01:33:25,000
(The undying crown prince of dance)

2720
01:33:25,670 --> 01:33:27,300
(I'm the heart-breaker of women)

2721
01:33:28,210 --> 01:33:29,870
(I never reverse when it comes to live)

2722
01:33:30,440 --> 01:33:32,240
(A pocket boy you want to put in your pocket)

2723
01:33:32,840 --> 01:33:34,650
(What I like is being with you)

2724
01:33:36,110 --> 01:33:41,190
(Enjoy the sentiments and feel of the past)

2725
01:33:42,690 --> 01:33:45,890
(The 1990s might suit me very well.)

2726
01:33:46,160 --> 01:33:47,220
I'm exhausted.

2727
